name: Soto Bandung
description: The soup is a clear beef soto that has pieces of meat, white radish, and fried soybeans.

name: Soto Banjar
description: The soup is spiced with star anise, clove, cassia and lemongrass, and sour hot sambal, served with potato cakes.

name: Pindang patin
description: This spicy and savory soup where the main ingredients of this dish are usually catfish with herbs and spices

name: Dhansak
description: The stew is made by cooking mutton or goat meat with a mixture of lentils and vegetable

name: Yin yang fried rice
description: This dish is a fried rice featuring bechamel sauce and tomato sauce.

name: Arroz caldoso
description: The dish consists of rice cooked in broth, with various seasonings and ingredients. The recipe varies by region, ranging from a risotto-like consistency to a rice soup or a dish resembling paella.

name: Arroz con huevo frito
description: The dish is made with rice with fried egg.

name: Arroz con maiz
description: The dish is made with rice and corn cooked in one pot.

name: Arroz de lisa
description: The dish is made with mullet, typically including Vegetable, and spices. It is usually served in a leaf with minced chives, accompanied by bollo, avocado salad, and guarapo.

name: Baghali polo
description: The dish consists of rice, fava beans and dill. It is made by cooking rice and green broad beans in boiling water. When cooked, the rice and beans are layered with dill in a pan, and everything is baked in an oven until ready. Saffron water can also be added to the rice.[1] It is typically served with meat. Like other Iranian traditional foods, the dish may be served at special occasions and family gatherings.

name: Bánh chưng
description: The dish is made from glutinous rice, mung beans, pork and other ingredients.

name: Bhakri
description: The dish is a round flatbread. It is coarser than a regular wheat flatbread. It can be either soft or hard in texture.

name: Chazuke
description: The dish is made by pouring green tea, dashi, or hot water over cooked rice. This dish provides a way to use leftover rice as a quick snack because it is easy to make.

name: Chelow
description: The dish is made with rice that is carefully prepared through soaking and parboiling, at which point the water is drained and the rice is steamed. This method results in an exceptionally fluffy rice with the grains separated and not sticky; it also results in a golden rice crust at the bottom of the pot.

name: Cơm tấm
description: The dish is made of rice with fractured rice grains.

name: Dal bhat
description: The dish consists of steamed rice and a cooked lentil or other pulses stew called dal.

name: Gaifan
description: The dish consists of a fish, meat, or vegetable topping served over rice. The dish can be either freshly cooked or previously cooked, such as char siu.

name: Gimbap
description: The dish is made from cooked rice, Vegetable, fish, and meat rolled in gim—dried sheets of seaweed—and served in bite-sized slices.

name: Jiuniang
description: The dish consists of a mixture of partially digested rice grains floating in a sweet saccharified liquid, with small amounts of alcohol and lactic acid. It is made by fermenting glutinous rice with a starter called jiuqu containing Rhizopus oryzae or Aspergillus oryzae and often yeast and bacteria.

name: Jhalmuri
description: The dish is a popular street snack, made of puffed rice and an assortment of Indian spices, Vegetable, Bombay mix and mustard oil..

name: Kabuli pulao
description: The dish core ingredients are steamed rice mixed with caramelized carrots and dry raisins as well as marinated lamb meat. Qabeli palaw is commonly garnished with almonds and pistachios. Saffron may be added to either the rice, the sauce or the garnishes.

name: Ketupat
description: The dish packed inside a diamond-shaped container of woven palm leaf pouch. It  is cut open until its skin (woven palm leaf) is totally removed. The inner rice cake is then cut into pieces and served as a staple food in place of plain steamed rice.

name: Khao lam
description: The dish consists of sticky rice roasted inside specially prepared bamboo sections of different diameters and lengths.

name: Kongbap
description: The dish consists of white or brown rice cooked together with one or more varieties of soybeans. It may be made from scratch by combining and cooking together dried rice and soybeans—usually black soybeans.

name: Madumongso
description: The dish is a snack made from black sticky rice as the main ingredient. The sweet flavour is a result of fermenting black sticky rice into tapai and then it is cooked to become dodol.

name: Tapai
description: The dish is a traditional fermented preparation of rice or other starchy foods. It has a sweet or sour taste[1] and can be eaten as is, as ingredients for traditional recipes, or fermented further to make rice wine.

name: Jaynagarer Moa
description: The dish is made from date palm jaggery and aromatic rice.

name: Mochi ice cream
description: The dish is made from pounded sticky rice with an ice cream filling.

name: Moffle
description: The dish consisting of mochi rice cake cooked in a waffle iron, which creates a waffle.

name: Nasi bogana
description: The dish is rice wrapped in banana leaves and served with a variety of side dishes. It is a type of mixed rice, which features rice accompanied by multiple side dishes.

name: Nasi jinggo
description: The dish consists of rice packaged in small portions of banana leaves.

name: Nasi kandar
description: The dish consists of steamed rice combined with an array of distinct curries, sides dishes, and gravies. The selection of curries consists of various blends of Vegetable, seafood or meat.

name: Nasi kapau
description: The dish is a steamed rice topped with various choices of dishes.

name: Nasi timbel
description: The dish consisting of steamed rice wrapped inside a banana leaf.The heat of the hot-cooked rice touches the banana leaf and produces a unique aroma.

name: Nasi tutug oncom
description: The dish is made of rice mixed with oncom fermented beans. It is usually wrapped in banana leaves and served with various side dishes.

name: Nurungji
description: The dish is made of scorched rice. After boiling and serving rice, a thin crust of scorched rice will usually be left in the bottom of the cooking pot.

name: Ofada rice
description: The dish is a type of rice. It is used in making a variety of dishes.

name: Okowa
description: The is a steamed rice dish made with glutinous rice mixed with meat or Vegetable.

name: Orez Shu'it
description: The dish consisting of white beans cooked in a tomato paste, served on white rice.

name: Pabellón criollo
description: It is a plate of rice, shredded beef in stew and stewed black beans.

name: Pinipig
description: The dish is a flattened rice ingredient. It is made of immature grains of glutinous rice pounded until flat before being toasted. It is commonly used as toppings for various desserts, but can also be eaten plain, made into cakes, or mixed with drinks and other dishes.

name: Pusô
description: The dish is a rice cake made by boiling rice in a woven pouch of palm leaves. It is most commonly found in octahedral, diamond, or rectangular shapes, but it can also come in various other intricately woven complex forms.

name: Puto bumbong
description: The dish is a purple rice cake steamed in bamboo tubes.

name: Rice and gravy
description: The dish is made by deglazing a pan to make brown gravy, simmering with extra seasonings, and serving over steamed or boiled rice.

name: Rice Krispies
description: The dish is a breakfast cereal made of crisped rice. When milk is added to the cereal the rice tends to collapse, creating the characteristic "snap", "crackle and pop" sounds.

name: Sel roti
description: The dish is a ring-shaped sweet fried dough made from rice flour.

name: Shirin polo
description: The dish is typically served at celebrations such as weddings, birthdays, and holidays. It is steamed rice topped with nuts and dried fruits such as barberries, apricots, and dates.

name: Thalassery biryani
description: The dish is a rice-based dish blended with spices and chicken.

name: Tinapayan
description: The dish consists of tapay (fermented cooked rice) and dried fish.

name: Tube rice pudding
description: The dish consists of a stir-fried glutinous rice mixture that is seasoned and steamed in a bamboo tube. This dish is a cylindrical shape caused by the steaming process in a tube.

name: Waakye
description: The dish is a cooked rice and beans covered with leaf sheaths.

name: Xôi
description: The dish is a savory glutinous rice covered with eggs and Vegetable.

name: Yakimochi
description: The dish is is grilled or broiled mochi or pounded rice cake. Traditionally, it is prepared using a small charcoal grill, but in modern times a gas grill can be used. During the time of the Autumn Moon, it is traditional to eat this dish while sipping sake and enjoying the view of the full moon.

name: Zosui
description: The dish is a mild and thin rice soup akin to a rice-based vegetable soup. It is made from pre-cooked rice and dashi or water seasoned with either soy sauce or miso and cooked with other ingredients such as meat, seafood, mushrooms, and Vegetable.

name: Ciba cake
description: The dish is made of glutinous rice pounded into paste and is often fried or steamed before being served. It is often molded into shapes of balls or cuboids.

name: Funing big cake
description: The dish traditionally use sticky rice, white sugar, and refined lard as  raw materials. Sometimes the dish also contains pine nuts, walnuts, or other ingredients as garnishes.

name: Qingtuan
description: The dish is made of glutinous rice mixed with matcha, with a wider variety of fillings, such as rousong or salted egg yolk.

name: White sugar sponge cake
description: The dish is white in color, with a spongy and soft consistency. The taste is sweet, and sometimes has a slightly sour taste due to fermentation of the batter prior to cooking.

name: Senbei
description: The dish is a rice cracker. They come in various shapes, sizes, and flavors, usually savory but sometimes sweet. This dish is often eaten with green tea as a casual snack and offered to visiting house guests as a courtesy refreshment.

name: Siru-tteok
description: The dish is a steamed rice cake made with red bean and rice.

name: Hwajeon
description: The dish is a pan-fried rice cake covered with edible petals.

name: Bánh tổ
description: The dish is made from glutinus irce flour with sticky sweet texture with brown color.

name: Chwee kueh
description: This is a steamed rice cake dish is served with preserved radish.

name: Rijstevlaai
description: The dish is a pie with a filling based on rice pudding.

name: Tangyuan
description: The dish is made of glutinous rice shaped into balls that are served in a hot broth or syrup. They come in varying sizes, anything between a marble to a ping pong ball, and are sometimes stuffed with filling.

name: Meghli
description: The dish is based on a floured rice pudding and spiced with anise, caraway, and cinnamon. The dish is often garnished with dried coconut flakes and various nuts including almonds, walnuts, pine nuts, and pistachios.

name: Chè
description: The dish is any sweet beverage, dessert soup or stew, or pudding. It includes a wide variety of distinct soups or puddings.

name: Ifumi
description: The dish served in a thick savoury sauce with pieces of meat or seafood and Vegetable. The dishes are to be served hot while the noodles are still crisp until the noodles are softened by the sauce and are ready to be eaten.

name: Buldak Ramen
description: The dish is a type of 'stir-fried' dry noodle: after boiling, the noodles are drained, and mixed with a spicy sauce and a topping.

name: Maggi goreng
description: The dish uses Maggi brand of instant noodles, prepared with hot water before stir-frying, instead of fresh yellow noodles.

name: Biangbiang noodles
description: The dish usually made using noodles that are thick and belt-like, and are usually hand-made.

name: Cart noodle
description: The dish is typically based upon the diner choosing various ingredients they would like, including the type of noodles, various soup broths, and toppings.Examples of types of noodles and toppings, which may vary considerably from stall to stall.

name: Hōtō
description: The dish is made by stewing flat udon noodles and Vegetable in miso soup. Though this dish is commonly recognized as a variant of udon, locals do not consider it to be an udon dish because the dough is prepared in the style of dumplings rather than noodles.

name: Otaru Ankake Yakisoba
description: The dish is a variety of stir-fried noodles with a starchy sauce. Each restaurant uses different recipes and ways of serving the dish, resulting in a wide range of flavours and variations on the dish.

name: Shirataki noodles
description: The dish is gelatinous noodles made from the corm of the konjac plant. In traditional cuisine, they are eaten in soups or stir-fried. The texture is chewy, similar to a tough jelly, and has little flavor before seasoning.

name: Tensoba
description: There are two varieties of the dish: one is served with a hot broth of dashi and soy sauce; the other is served with cooled soba and dipped in tsukejiru (lit. "dipping sauce"), either chilled or hot and usually strongly flavored.

name: Bibim guksu
description: The dish is a cold spicy noodle dish made with very thin wheat flour noodles called somyeon with added flavorings.

name: Toshikoshi soba
description: The dish is a noodle soup dish traditionally eaten on omisoka (new year's eve).

name: Jat-guksu
description: The dish consists of wheat flour or buckwheat noodles in a bowl of cold broth made from ground pine nuts.

name: Naengmyeon
description: The dish consists of long and thin handmade noodles made from the flour and starch of various ingredients, including buckwheat (메밀, memil), potatoes, sweet potatoes, arrowroot starch (darker color and chewier than buckwheat noodles), and kudzu (칡, chik). The dish usually served with cold broth.

name: Milmyeon
description: The dish consists of wheat noodles in a cold meat broth or a spicy sauce, and topped with Vegetable and garnish.

name: Chow mein sandwich
description: The dish consists of a brown gravy-based chow mein mixture placed between halves of a hamburger-style bun.

name: Käsespätzle
description: Hot spätzle and grated cheese such as Emmentaler or granular cheese are layered alternately and finally topped with fried onions. After adding each layer, the dish is baked until all the cheese is melted. Accompanying side dishes are green salads or potato salad.

name: Kraft Dinner
description: The dish is a nonperishable, packaged macaroni and cheese product.

name: Bún ốc
description: The dish contains broth, snails, and tofu as its basic characteristics but it can also contain green bananas, some fresh Vegetable or chopped water spinach, bean sprouts, water dropwort, tomatoes, and other ingredients.

name: Tsukemen
description: The dish consists of noodles that are eaten after being dipped in a separate bowl of soup or broth.

name: Abura Soba
description: The dish consists of dry noodle made with a sauce of soy sauce and lard.

name: Thenthuk
description: The noodle dish is made of wheat flour dough, mixed Vegetable and some pieces of mutton or yak meat.

name: Thukpa bhatuk
description: The dish is made of noodle. Meat is usually a main ingredient in this soup, commonly mutton, beef or yak; however, this soup can also be made vegetarian with a vegetable bouillon.

name: Saimin
description: The dish is made of soft wheat egg noodles served in a hot dashi garnished with diced green onions and a thin slice of kamaboko. It may also include additional toppings such as char siu, sliced Spam, sliced egg, bok choy, mushrooms, or shredded nori.

name: Cotoletta alla milanese
description: The dish consists of veal rib chop or sirloin bone-in and made into a breaded cutlet, fried in butter.

name: Krupuk
description: The dish is a deep fried crackers made from starch and other ingredients that serve as flavouring.

name: Khinkali
description: The dish is made of twisted knobs of dough, stuffed with meat, fish or Vegetable and spices.

name: Momo
description: The dumplings are prepared with ground/minced meat, potatoes, and leek filling.

name: Buuz
description: The dish is steamed dumpling filled with meat.

name: Siomay
description: The dish is a steamed fish dumpling with Vegetable served in peanut sauce.

name: Dorayaki
description: The dish consists of two small pancake-like patties made from castella wrapped around a filling of sweet bean paste.

name: Buchimgae
description: The dish made by pan-frying a thick batter mixed with egg and other ingredients until a thin flat pancake-shaped fritter is formed.

name: Bindae-tteok
description: The dish is made by grinding soaked mung beans, adding vegetable and meat and pan-frying it into a round, flat shape.

name: Murtabak
description: The dish is often described as spicy folded omelette pancake with bits of vegetable. The most common form of this dish is made from pan fried crepes usually stuffed with beaten eggs, chopped leeks, chives, or green onion (scallions) and minced meat, which is then folded and cut to squares.

name: Chataamari
description: The dish is made of rice crepe with meat and egg topping.

name: Pisang Molen
description: The dish is a fritter made by deep frying battered banana or plantain in hot cooking oil.

name: Maruya
description: The dish is made by bananas cooked with batter.

name: Kluai khaek
description: The dish is made from fried, floured banana commonly topped with white sesame.

name: chuối chiên
description: The dish after deep frying, banana fritters are drizzled with rum or rice wine and ignited to further crisp them.

name: Doenjang jjigae
description: This dish is made from the primary ingredient of soybean paste, and additional optional ingredients Vegetable, seafood, and meat.

name: Douhua
description: This dish is a sweet or savoury snack made with silken tofu. It is also referred to as tofu pudding, soybean pudding, or tofu brains.

name: Ganmodoki
description: The dish is a fried tofu fritter made with Vegetable such as carrots, lotus roots, and burdock with sometimes egg.

name: Kupat tahu
description: The dish is a rice cake served with peanut sauce topped with crispy crackers.

name: Stinky tofu
description: This dish is a form of fermented tofu that has a strong odor. It is usually sold at night markets or roadside stands as a snack, or in lunch bars as a side dish, rather than in restaurants. Traditionally the dish is fermented in a brine with Vegetable and meat, sometimes for months.

name: Taho
description: The dish is made from soft tofu with sweet brown-colored sugar syrup and sago pearls.

name: Tahu sumedang
description: The dish is made of deep-fried tofu, usually served with separate green chili.

name: Corunda
description: The dish is wrapped in a long corn or reed plant leaf, and folded, making a triangular shape or spherical shape. They are typically steamed until golden and eaten with sour cream and red salsa.

name: Andong jjimdak
description: This dish is a stew made with chicken, various Vegetable marinated in a soy sauce based sauce.

name: Galbi-jjim
description: This dish is a stew made with short rib, generally beef or pork.

name: Urap
description: The dish is a salad dish of steamed Vegetable mixed with seasoned and spiced grated coconut for dressing.

name: Mantau
description: The dish is a white and soft type of steamed bread or bun. It is made with milled wheat flour, water and leavening agents.

name: Tingmo
description: The dish is a steamed bun with shape similar to flower rolls with soft and fluffy texture.

name: Wotou
description: The dish is a type of steamed bread made from cornmeal.

name: Baozi
description: This dish is a type of yeast-leavened filled bun. There are many variations in fillings (meat or vegetarian) and preparations, though the buns are most often steamed.

name: Gaobuli
description: This dish is a bun with wrinkles on the outside.

name: Shengjian mantou
description: This dish is a small, pan-fried bun with pork filling.

name: Tangbao
description: This dish is a soup buns, a large, soup-filled buns made by wrapping dough which then steamed into soup.

name: Hoppang
description: This dish is a convenience food version of steamed bread and is typically filled with smooth, sweetened red bean paste.

name: Jjinppang
description: This dish is a steamed bun, typically filled with red bean paste with bits of broken beans and bean husk.

name: Lotus seed bun
description: This dish is a steamed yeast-leavened dough that contains lotus seed paste.

name: Longevity peach
description: This dish is a white bun with red dyed tip with a crease along the side, mimicking shape of the peach.

name: Mandarin roll
description: The dish is a steamed white-colored bun with a twisted shape.

name: Taro cake
description: The dish is a dense texture cake made from vegetable taro, cut into rectangular slices and pan-fried.

name: Treacle sponge pudding
description: The dish is a steamed sponge cake with treacle cooked on top of it.

name: Karukan
description: The dish is a traditional confection in the form of a long block.

name: Kue mangkok
description: The dish is a traditional steamed cupcake that requires few ingredients, typically around four to five, and is cooked by steaming.

name: Seri muka
description: The dish is a two-layered dessert with steamed glutinous rice at the bottom and a green pandan-flavored custard on top.

name: Lucky tattie
description: The dish is made of a white fondant solid core flavoured with cassia, and steamed and covered with cinnamon powder.

name: Chawanmushi
description: The dish is a savory egg custard made by steaming an egg mixture flavored with soy sauce, dashi, and mirin.

name: Eo-mandu
description: The dish is a half-moon-shaped dumpling prepared with filleted whitefish, most typically brown croakers, instead of flour dough as the wrapping.

name: Har gow
description: The dish is a traditional dumpling served as dim sum. It is made of shrimp meat, and steamed in a flour wrapper. After cooking, the wrapper becomes somewhat translucent.

name: Steamed cheeseburger
description: This dish is a type of hamburger topped with cheese that is cooked via steaming.

name: Cabinet pudding
description: The dish is a steamed, sweet, moulded pudding made from some combination of bread or sponge cake or similar ingredients in custard, cooked in a mould faced with decorative fruit pieces such as cherries or raisins, served with some form of sweet sauce.

name: Jeungpyeon
description: The dish is made by steaming rice flour dough prepared with makgeolli (rice wine).

name: Mujigae-tteok
description: The dish is a layered tteok (rice cake) of different colors resembling a rainbow.

name: Bappir
description: The dish is a twice-baked barley bread.

name: Fat rascal
description: The dish baked as a buttery, flat cake baked in a covered pan among the ashes of a peat fire.

name: Paximathia
description: The dish is a hard bread that is prepared with whole wheat, chick pea or barley flour.

name: Aachener Printen
description: This pastry is originally sweetened with honey, but are now generally sweetened with a syrup made from sugar beets.

name: Abernethy biscuit
description: The dish is a type of digestive biscuit, a baked good originally designed to be eaten as a support to proper digestion.

name: Acıbadem kurabiyesi
description: The dish is a biscuit made of almonds, sugar and egg whites. The traditional recipes include a small amount of bitter almonds

name: Amaretti di Saronno
description: The dish is a type of amaretto, a bitter-sweet flavored macaroon. It is one of many types of traditional amaretti, but the only one made with apricot kernels (the others are usually made with almonds).

name: Aparon
description: This dish is a wafer drizzled with caramelized sugar and optionally, sesame seeds. It is uniquely made from unconsecrated communion wafers.

name: Basler Läckerli
description: The dish is made by baking a thin layer of dough, which is then topped with a sugar glaze while still hot and cut into rectangular pieces.

name: Berger Cookies
description: The dish is frosted on its flat bottom, giving the final cookie an overall rounded shape. Each weighs 1.25 ounces, with the cake-like under-cookie weighing a quarter of an ounce, and the chocolate/fudge frosting weighing an ounce.

name: Bourbon biscuit
description: The dish is a sandwich biscuit consisting of two thin rectangular dark chocolate-flavoured biscuits with a chocolate buttercream filling.

name: Camachile cookie
description: The dish is characteristically shaped like the fruits of the camachile tree (Pithecellobium dulce).

name: Carrot cake cookie
description: The dish is cake that contains carrots mixed into the batter.

name: Cat tongue
description: The dish is a small, long, and flat biscuit resembling a cat's tongue.

name: Caycay
description: The dish is a crunchy layered cookie coated in syrup (latik) or honey and rolled in coarsely ground toasted peanuts.

name: Chocolate-coated marshmallow treats
description: The dish is a confection consisting of a biscuit base topped with marshmallow-like filling and then coated in a hard shell of chocolate.

name: Custard cream
description: The dish is a type of sandwich biscuit filled with a creamy, custard-flavoured centre.

name: Drabbelkoek
description: The dish is a sort of round and hard cookie which made by dribbling strings of the liquid dough in hot butter.

name: Fig roll
description: The dish is a biscuit or cookie consisting of a rolled cake or pastry filled with fig paste.

name: Finskepinner
description: The dish is a shortbread cookie characterized by its long shape, crispy texture, and its frequent consumption during Christmas.

name: Fudge cookie
description: The dish is a is a cookie that is prepared with fudge or that has the flavor, consistency or texture of fudge.

name: Galletas de patatas
description: The dish is a thick and square-shaped biscuit with upturned edges.

name: Garibaldi biscuit
description: The dish consists of currants squashed and sandwiched between two thin oblongs of biscuit dough before baking.

name: Gazelle ankles
description: The dish is a crescent-shaped cookies made of flour-based dough filled with almond paste aromatized with orange blossom water.

name: Qurabiya
description: The dish is a shortbread-type biscuit, usually made with ground almonds.

name: Gingerbread man
description: The dish is a biscuit or cookie made from gingerbread, usually in the shape of a stylized human being following seasonal themes.

name: Half-moon cookie
description: The dish  is a semicircle- or crescent-shaped butter cookie. It has a soft crumbly texture and a sweet flavor with a salty aftertaste.

name: Jacobina
description: The dish is a biscuit that are distinctively cubical in shape.

name: Jammie Dodgers
description: The dish is a  biscuit made from shortcake with a raspberry or strawberry flavoured jam filling.

name: Jodenkoek
description: The dish is a big, flat, round shortbread biscuit with a diameter of about 10 centimeters (4").

name: Kaasstengels
description: The dish is a cheese snack in the shape of sticks. It tastes savoury and salty instead of sweet.

name: Kahk
description: The dish is a small circular biscuit. It is covered with powdered sugar and can be stuffed with ʿagameyya (a mixture of honey, nuts, and ghee), lokum, walnuts, pistachios, or dates, or simply served plain.

name: Kiâm-piánn
description: The dish is a biscuit which is characterized by a crispy texture and a savory taste with a hint of pepper, which becomes subtly sweet upon chewing.

name: Kue gapit
description: This dish is a kind of cracker generally made from tapioca flour. Its name comes from the cooking process, in which it is grilled between iron molds like a waffle.

name: Kue satu
description: This dish is a traditional cookie made of sweet white-colored mung bean powder that crumbles when bitten.

name: Lincoln biscuit
description: The dish is a circular shortcake biscuit, most commonly decorated on one side with a pattern of raised dots.

name: Maple leaf cream cookie
description: The dish is a sandwich cookies. The cream filling is maple-flavoured, and may contain real maple syrup.

name: Paciencia
description: The dish is made from beaten egg whites, flour, and calamansi with hemispherical shape.

name: Petit-Beurre
description: The dish is a type of shortbread surface of the biscuit is smooth and has twenty-four indents (four lines with six columns) intermixed with the inscription of the dish name in three lines.

name: Pepernoot
description: The dish is light brown, square shaped, and made from the same ingredients as taai-taai: rye flour, sugar and anise, and sometimes also cinnamon, and clove. They are fairly chewy, though they harden gradually when exposed to the air.

name: Pinolate
description: The dish is a type of cookie light golden color and studded with golden pine nuts (pinoli in Italian). Made with almond paste and egg whites, they are moist, soft and chewy.

name: Piñata cookie
description: The dish is a sugar cookie that is shaped and colored like a rainbow colored horse and filled with various small candies which spill out when the cookie is broken.

name: Kue putri salju
description: The dish is dried cake shaped like crescents and covered with powdered sugar.

name: Kue semprong
description: The dish is a wafer snack made by clasping egg batter using an iron mold (Waffle iron) which is heated up on a charcoal stove.

name: Silvana
description: The dish is frozen cookie consisting of a layer of buttercream sandwiched between two cashew-meringue wafers coated with cookie crumbs.

name: Spritzgebäck
description: The dish is a type biscuit or cookie made of a rich shortcrust pastry. When made correctly, the cookies are crisp, fragile, somewhat dry, and buttery.

name: Teiglach
description: The dish is small, knotted pastries boiled in a honeyed syrup.

name: Tirggel
description: The dish is made from flour and honey, they are thin, hard, and sweet.

name: Ugoy-ugoy
description: The dish is a type of layered biscuits. They are typically rectangular or ribbon-like in shape and are topped with granulated sugar.

name: Uraro
description: The dish is made from cassava like flour. They have a dry and powdery texture and are usually flower-shaped.

name: E.L. Fudge
description: The dish is a type of butter-flavored shortbread sandwich cookies with a fudge creme filling.

name: Hello Panda
description: The dish is a type of filling biscuits, each biscuit consists of a small hollow shortbread layer, filled with crème of various flavors. On some biscuits are printed cartoon style depictions of giant pandas doing various activities, such as fencing and archery, and also in the United States, other activities such as hockey and baseball.

name: Lorna Doone
description: The dish is a brand of golden, square-shaped shortbread cookie.

name: Viennese whirls
description: The dish is a type of biscuit consisting of soft shortbread cakes piped into a whirl shape and come in various shapes with different fillings and decorations.

name: Alexandertorte
description: The dish is a cake that consists of pastry strips filled with raspberry preserves or raspberry jam. It is traditionally eaten as a dessert after lunch or dinner, but it can also be served at tea time. It should be made a day or so before it is planned to serve, because the icing must be hard before the cake is cut.

name: Bahulu
description: The dish is a type of pastry. There are three versions available, the most common being star-shaped and the more elusive shaped like rolls and layered.

name: Bakewell pudding
description: The dish is a type of dessert consisting of a flaky pastry base with a layer of sieved jam and topped with a filling made of egg and almond paste.

name: Bakpia pathok
description: The dish usually stuffed with mung beans, but have recently come in other fillings as well, e.g. chocolate, durian and cheese.

name: Bichon au citron
description: The dish is a pastry that it is made of puff pastry. A major distinguishing feature is that it is filled with lemon curd. The outer layer of sugar is sometimes partially caramelized.

name: Birnbrot
description: The dish is a bread with a filling of dried pears. Besides dried pears the filling also contains raisins, walnuts and other dried fruit such as apples or figs. The filling is additionally flavored with candied fruit, coriander, cinnamon, star anise, anise, clove and some sort of alcohol.

name: Bizcocho
description: The dish is the name given range of pastries, cakes or cookies.

name: Bossche bol
description: The dish is effectively a large filled choux pastry, about 12 cm in diameter, filled with whipped cream and coated entirely or almost entirely with (usually dark) chocolate fondant icing.

name: Bougatsa
description: The dish is a breakfast food (sweet or savoury), or mid-morning snack, or midday snack. It has several versions with their own filling, with the most popular the cream that has semolina custard filling used as a sweet food and dessert.

name: Boyoz
description: The dish is a pastry. The most widely preferred is plain, without addition of meat or cheese or spinach stuffings.

name: Cheesymite scroll
description: The dish is a savoury baked food. It consists of a spiral of baked bread similar to a pain aux raisins with a thick, dark brown food spread and cheese in place of raisins.

name: Chouquette
description: The dish are small pieces of pastry consisting of small spheres of choux pastry, sugared and baked. The dish was known in the 16th century, and was originally applied to small savoury spheres. Since the late 17th century it have been sweet.

name: Conversation tart
description: The dish is a type of tart made with puff pastry that is filled with sweet almond custard cream and topped with royal icing.

name: Crêpes Suzette
description: The dish is a dessert consisting of crepes with a sauce of caramelized sugar and butter, tangerine or orange juice, zest, and orange liqueur on top.

name: Crocetta di Caltanissetta
description: The dish is a traditional sweet pastry. It is made by almonds, sugar, sweet lemon purée, oranges or other fruit typical of the area, pistachio and icing sugar.

name: Flaugnarde
description: The dish is a baked dessert with fruit arranged in a buttered dish and covered with a thick flan-like batter. It is made with apples, peaches, pears, plums, prunes or other fruits. Resembling a sweet batter pudding or large pancake, the dish is dusted with confectioner's sugar and can be served either warm or cold.

name: Flies' graveyard
description: The dish is nicknames of pastry, for sweet pastries filled with currants or raisins, which are jokingly said to resemble dead flies.

name: Gibanica
description: The dish is usually made with cottage cheese and eggs. Recipes can range from sweet to savoury, and from simple to festive and elaborate multi-layered cakes.

name: Gustavus Adolphus pastry
description: The dish is a pastry. Recipes for the pastry vary locally but most versions have a portrait of the king on the top, usually made of chocolate or marzipan.

name: Hwangnam-ppang
description: The dish is a small pastry with a filling of red bean paste. It is made from a mixture of eggs and wheat flour, with the red bean filling being almost 70% of the pastry. A chrysanthemum would be traditionally imprinted on the top.

name: Haddekuche
description: The dish is a traditional pastry that resembles with a diamond-themed pattern imprinted on the pastry itself.

name: Heong Peng
description: These pastries, which resemble slightly flattened balls, contain a sweet sticky filling made from malt and shallots, which is covered by a flaky baked crust and garnished with sesame seeds on the surface.

name: Joulutorttu
description: The dish is a pastry. It is traditionally made from puff pastry in the shape of a star or pinwheel and filled with prune jam and often dusted with icing sugar. The pastries can be in other shapes and apple used in place of the prune jam.

name: Karakudamono
description: The dish is a term used to refer to various pastry desserts originating from another country.

name: Kok
description: The dish is a profiterole consisting of pastry cream, chocolate glaze and syrup. It is sometimes additionally topped with nuts or flakes of various kinds.

name: Kringlea
description: The dish is a pastry, a variety of pretzel. It denotes the pretzel-like knotted shape rather than the pretzel pastry type. It may be made from puff pastry (like Danish pastry) or yeast dough, filled with remonce or marzipan and raisins, sprinkled with coarse sugar, nut flakes or icing.

name: Kroštule
description: The dish is a traditional pastry. It is made from deep frying dough.

name: Kūčiukai
description: The dish is small, slightly sweet pastries made from leavened dough and poppy seeds. They vary in sweetness and are usually eaten dry but can be served soaked in poppy milk or with cranberry pudding.

name: Lady's navel
description: The dish is a type of sweet pastry. They are made from balls of choux pastry which are given a dimple, deep-fried and then soaked in syrup.

name: Leipziger Lerche
description: The dish is a pastry. The dish used the actual songbird lark, which was roasted with herbs and eggs and served as a filling in a pastry crust. Today's version consists of a shortcrust filled with a mixture of crushed almonds, nuts and a cherry. The cherry symbolises the heart of the bird. It is topped with a grid of two crossed dough strips.

name: Le̍k-tāu-phòng
description: It is a traditional mooncake. The filling is made of sweet green gram paste stuffed with lard and shallots and baked, and sometimes a little pork is added. In recent years, due to the emphasis on health, many operators have also introduced versions that do not contain pork, lard and other ingredients, and are purely filled with mung bean puree.

name: Makroudh
description: The dish is a cookie. It is filled with dates and nuts or almond paste, that has a diamond shape – the name derives from this characteristic shape. The dough is made with a combination of semolina and flour, which gives the pastry a very specific texture and flavor.

name: Naiyou subing
description: The dish is a buttery flaky pastry made into a thin circle. The dough has many layers, of which each is very thin and crisp. The filling is composed of butter and maltose.

name: Ox-tongue pastry
description: The dish is a pastry. It is a fried dough food that is elliptical in shape and resembles an ox tongue or a horse ear. The pastry texture is chewy, with a soft interior and a crunchy crust. It is lightly sweetened, and eaten as part of breakfast with soy milk.

name: Pain aux raisins
description: The dish is a spiral pastry often eaten for breakfast. It is typically made with a leavened butter pastry with raisins added and shaped in a spiral with custard filling.

name: Paper wrapped cake
description: The dish is a type of cake. In essence, it is a chiffon cake baked in a paper cup. Traditionally prepared wrapped cakes are usually steamed in a wok pan. The cakes are typically prepared by separating the egg yolks and whites, and whisking them separately as well.

name: Pastizz
description: The dish is a traditional savoury pastry. It is usually have a filling either of cheese or curried peas. They are usually diamond-shaped or round. The pastry is folded in different ways according to the filling, as a means of identification. Traditionally, the cheese one are folded down the middle, whereas pea one are folded down the side.

name: Plăcintă
description: This dish is a and traditional pastry resembling a thin, small round or square-shaped cake, usually filled with apples or a soft cheese such.

name: Prekmurska gibanica
description: The dish is a type of layered pastry. It contains poppy seeds, walnuts, apples, raisins and quark fillings.

name: Punsch-roll
description: The dish is a small cylindrical pastry covered with green marzipan with the ends dipped in chocolate, with an interior consisting of a mix of crushed biscuits, butter, and cocoa, flavoured with punsch liqueur.

name: Punschkrapfen
description: The dish is a nougat and jam filled sponge cake soaked with rum. It is a cake consisting of either sponge cake or cake crumbs, nougat chocolate and apricot jam. The Cake layers are soaked with rum.

name: Roze koek
description: The dish is a pastry. It consists of a round, flat, dense cake with a layer of pink fondant icing, similar to black and white cookies. On occasion the cakes are sold in alternative varieties, with the pink icing replaced by a different colour.

name: Runeberg torte
description: The dish is a torte flavored with almonds and arrack or rum and weighing about 100 grams. It usually has raspberry jam encircled by a ring of icing on top.

name: Xuixo
description: The dish is a deep-fried, sugar-coated cylindrical pastry filled with crema catalana. Commonly eaten for breakfast or tea.

name: Schaumrolle
description: The dish is a confection. They consist of a cone or tube of puff pastry filled with whipped cream or meringue. They are about 3 inches (7.6 cm) wide. The pastries are made by wrapping thin pastry strips around a cone shaped metal tube. After baking, they are filled with the "foam", which is usually sweetened whipped cream or meringue. The pastry tubes are often rolled in coarse sugar or powdered sugar before baking, for extra sweetness and a crunchy texture.

name: Schneeball
description: The dish is a deep-fried pastry made from shortcrust pastry. Its name derives from its round, ball-like shape, its diameter of about eight to ten centimeters, and its traditional decoration with white confectioner's sugar.

name: Schuxen
description: The dish is an elongate fried dough pastry made from rye flour and yeast. Nowadays they are rare, and few bakers produce them.

name: Sfințișori
description: The dish is traditional pastry. Shape the dough into large shapes of the figure 8, bake and coat with honey and walnuts.

name: Stutenkerl
description: The dish is a pastry made of sweet leavened dough, in the form of a man. The pastry often features raisins in the place of eyes and a clay pipe.

name: Sufganiyah
description: The dish is a round jelly doughnut. The doughnut is deep-fried, injected with jam or custard, and then topped with powdered sugar.

name: Suncake
description: The dish is a popular dessert. The typical fillings consist of maltose (condensed malt sugar), and they are usually sold in special gift boxes as souvenirs for visitors. They are round, and they may vary in size. They are characterized by flaky crusts. Most people eat them with tea, and some people dissolve them in hot water to make a porridge-like dessert.

name: Taro pastry
description: The dish is a shortbread snack with a spherical shape and made with taro as sweet filling. The main method of making it is to wrap the pastry made with flour and butter with the filling made of taro puree and place it in the oven.

name: Roscón
description: The dish is a sweet bread-based ring-shaped dessert.

name: Tortita negra
description: The dish is a pastry which is flat at its base and round on the sides. Traditionally they have dark brown sugar on the top.They are usually the perfect accompaniment to mate in the morning or in the afternoon during "tea time". They are a popular food at children's parties

name: Yau gok
description: A dumpling which its wrap is first made of glutinous rice dough. A crescent shape is formed to hold the fried ingredients used as filling. A batch of the pastries are either baked or deep fried in a wok.

name: Killie pie
description: A steak and gravy pie.

name: Blackberry pie
description: A pie composed of blackberry filling, usually in the form of either blackberry jam, actual blackberries themselves, or some combination thereof.

name: Buko pie
description: A pie made with young coconuts, and uses sweetened condensed milk, which makes it denser than cream-based custard pies.

name: Bündner Nusstorte
description: A traditional sweet, caramelised nut-filled pastry (generally walnut).

name: Chicken and mushroom pie
description: The outside is usually a full top and bottom crust, with the filling made up of small pieces of chicken and sliced mushrooms in a creamy sauce. The top crust is typically puff pastry. Variations on the theme can use nutmeg or spring onion as part of the creamy filling.

name: Chicken pastel
description: A traditional stew or pie made with chicken, sausages, mushrooms, peas, carrots, potatoes, soy sauce, and various spices in a creamy sauce.

name: Fleischkuekle
description: A deep fried turnover which has typically ground or minced meat and onions as a filling.

name: Grape hull pie
description: The pie is prepared by simmering the skins of muscadine grapes together with sugar, grape pulp and lemon juice. Seeds are removed from the mixture by straining or picking them out. The filling is then poured into a double pie crust and baked.

name: Homity pie
description: Open vegetable pie which case contains a filling of potatoes and an onion and leek mixture, which is then covered with cheese.

name: Jamaican patty
description: A semicircular pastry that contains various fillings and spices baked inside a flaky shell, often tinted golden yellow with an egg yolk mixture or turmeric.

name: Manchester tart
description: A shortcrust pastry shell spread with raspberry jam, covered with a custard filling and topped with flakes of coconut and a Maraschino cherry.

name: Melton Mowbray pork pie
description: The uncured meat of this pie is grey in colour when cooked and the meat is chopped, rather than minced. As the pies are baked free-standing, the sides bow outwards, rather than being vertical as with mould-baked pies.

name: Moravian chicken pie
description: A savory meat pie which is a double crusted pie made with flaky shortcrust pastry filled with only chunks of poached chicken meat and a thick broth-based sauce. Unlike chicken pot pies, Vegetable are never included in the filling. The pie is served in slices with hot chicken gravy on top, and extra gravy on the side.

name: Pie à la Mode
description: A pie served with ice cream.

name: Rhubarb pie
description: A pie with a rhubarb filling.

name: Soparnik
description: It is a savoury pie made from common ingredients from the region: Chard with onions and parsley between two layers of simplest dough. Among the numerous local variations there are also sweet ones, for example with nuts, dried fruits or caramel.

name: Speķrauši
description: Oblong or crescent-shaped baked bread rolls or pastries filled with finely chopped fatty bacon cubes and onions.

name: Stargazy pie
description: A pastry-based fish pie which, by tradition, is filled with whole pilchards. It is critical that the pilchards retain their heads, so they poke through the pastry top. The appearance of the fish heads makes them look like they are "gazing at the stars". The position of the fish allows the oil that is released during cooking to drain into the pie, adding a fuller flavour and ensuring the pie is moist.

name: Tarta capuchina
description: A cake made mainly with egg yolk and syryp using water bath. The cake is usually presented in a cylindrical or rectangle shape, depending on the mold. It is commonly served at room temperature.

name: Wähe
description: This dish consists of a casing (typically made of shortcrust pastry, but sometimes yeast dough or puff pastry) and a topping of a custard enveloping either fruit, Vegetable or cheese.

name: Woolton pie
description: A pastry dish of Vegetable. The recipe involved dicing and cooking potatoes (or parsnips), cauliflower, carrots and possibly turnip. Other Vegetable were added where available.

name: Anpan
description: Sweet roll most commonly filled with red bean paste. It can also be prepared with other fillings, including white beans, green beans, sesame, and chestnuts.

name: Balep korkun
description: A type of bread that is round, flat and relatively easy to make. The ingredients are barley flour, water and baking powder. It is cooked in a frying pan.

name: Barm cake
description: A soft, round, flattish bread item, traditionally leavened with barm.

name: Saj bread
description: Unleavened flatbread baked on a metal griddle.

name: Vienna bread
description: Bread that used high milling of Hungarian grain, and cereal press-yeast for leavening.

name: Tiger bread
description: The bread is generally made with a pattern baked onto the top made by painting rice paste onto the surface prior to baking.The rice paste that imparts the bread's characteristic flavour dries and cracks during the baking process. The bread itself has a crusty exterior, but is soft inside. Typically, it is made as a white bread bloomer loaf or bread roll, but the technique can be applied to any shape of bread.

name: Tandoor bread
description: A bread baked in a clay oven which is distinguishable based on the aroma, smell, appearance, color, size and overall texture.

name: Taboon bread
description: A flatbread baked in a clay oven. It is used as a base or wrap in many cuisines, and eaten with different accompaniments.

name: Sprouted bread
description: A type of bread made from whole grains that have been allowed to sprout (i.e., to germinate before being milled into flour). There are a few different types, some are made with additional added flour, some are made with added gluten, etc.

name: Spelt bread
description: Bread made from unripe spelt flour.

name: Shuangbaotai
description: A sweet fried dough containing large air pockets on the inside and a crisp crust on the outside. It is made by twisting two small pieces of dough together and frying them, causing them to separate slightly while remaining connected.

name: Bolani
description: A stuffed flat-bread, fried with a filling. It has a thin crust and can be stuffed with a variety of ingredients, such as potatoes or leeks but also grated pumpkin, chives, red lentils or with minced meat.

name: Bolillo
description: A type of savory bread, often baked in a stone oven. It is roughly 15 centimeters (5.9 in) long, in the shape of an ovoid, with a crunchy crust and a soft inside. It has a slash on top made with a slashing tool or bread lame, which permits the exhaust of steam and the expansion of bread without stressing its skin.

name: Carrot bread
description: A quick bread or yeast-leavened bread, that uses carrots as the primary ingredient. It may be prepared with grated, shredded carrots, or carrot juice. Baking times can vary depending on the amount of juice in the carrots used, and it may be a moist bread.

name: Česnica
description: Bread made with wheat flour and water. A coin is often put into the dough during the kneading; other small objects may also be inserted.

name: Christmas wafer
description: This dish is baked from pure wheat flour and water, are usually rectangular in shape and very thin; they are identical in composition to the altar bread.

name: Cottage loaf
description: The bread is characterised by its shape, which is essentially that of two round loaves, one on top of the other, with the upper one being smaller

name: Egg waffle
description: A spherical waffle consisting of an eggy leavened batter cooked between two plates of semi-spherical cells. They are usually served hot, and often eaten plain, although they may be served with fruit and flavors such as strawberry, coconut or chocolate.

name: Flatkaka
description: Unleavened rye flatbread that is soft, round, thin and dark with a characteristic pattern from the pan. Traditionally, it was baked on hot stones or straight on the embers of the fire, later on small but heavy cast iron frying pans, and today, when making the dish at home, people sometimes bake them directly on an electric hot plate to get the desired result.

name: Fugazza
description: A thick pizza crust topped with onions, cheese, and sometimes olives. It is derived from a combination of Neapolitan pizza with Italian focaccia bread.

name: Guokui
description: The dish is a kind of flatbread made from flour. The dish is said to have been invented by a laborer who cooked flatbread in his iron helmet over a wood fire. It is round in shape, about a foot long in diameter, an inch in thickness, and weighs about 2.5 kg.

name: Hardtack
description: The dish is a type of dense biscuit or cracker made from flour, water, and sometimes salt. It is inexpensive and long-lasting. It is used for sustenance in the absence of perishable foods, commonly during long sea voyages, land migrations, and military campaigns.

name: Ka'ak
description: The dish refer to several different types of baked goods. The bread is similar to a dry and hardened biscuit and mostly ring-shaped.

name: Khanom bueang
description: The dish is an ancient snack known as crispy pancakes. It is a popular form of street food. These crepes resemble tacos. They are usually first topped or filled with meringue, followed by sweet or salty toppings such as shredded coconut, strips of fried eggs or egg yolks, or chopped scallions.

name: Khakhra
description: The dish is a thin cracker. It is made from mat bean, wheat flour and oil.

name: Lagana
description: The dish is a flatbread. Traditionally, it was prepared unleavened (without the yeast), but leavened is nowadays more common. It is typically flat, oval-shaped, with surface decorated by impressing fingertips.

name: Laufabrauð
description: The dish is a traditional kind of bread. It consists of round, very thin flat cakes with a diameter of about 15 to 20 cm (6 to 8 inches), decorated with leaf-like, geometric patterns and fried briefly in hot tallow or oil.

name: Lavash
description: This dish is a thin flatbread that is usually leavened. Traditionally the dough is rolled out flat and slapped against the hot walls of a clay oven, but modern recipes may adapt for cooking on a wok.

name: Lye roll
description: The dish is typically covered with salt, preferably pretzel salt.

name: Mohnflesserl
description: The dish is in the form of a braided bun. It is typically sprinkled with poppy seeds , salt, and sometimes served glazed.

name: Michetta
description: The dish is a bread recognizable by its bulged shape.

name: Melonpan
description: The dish is a sweetbun covered in a layer of crispy cookie dough.

name: Shotis puri
description: The dish is a bread made of white flour and shaped like a canoe.

name: Shaobing
description: The dish is a type of baked, unleavened, layered flatbread. It is can be made with or without stuffing, and with or without sesame on top.

name: Sangak
description: The dish is is a plain, rectangular or triangular whole wheat leavened flatbread.

name: Salt-rising bread
description: The dish is a dense white bread leavened by naturally occurring wild bacteria rather than by yeast.

name: Samoon
description: The dish is a type of yeast bread. It is baked in traditional stone ovens.

name: Manda roti
description: This dish is extremely thin and limp, and served folded like a handkerchief.

name: Rugbrød
description: The dish is made with rye flour as the basic ingredient, which produces a plain or "old-fashioned" bread with a uniform, somewhat heavy structure.

name: Roti buaya
description: The dish is two piece sweetened bread in the shape of a crocodile.

name: Pane di Altamura
description: The dish is a type of naturally leavened bread made from remilled durum wheat semolina.

name: Pain de mie
description: The dish is a white or brown bread with a thin, soft crust.

name: Papadam
description: The dish is made from dough of black gram bean flour, which is either deep fried or cooked with dry heat by being flipped over an open flame until crunchy.

name: Peg bread
description: The dish is a bread that usually served along with tea in the morning.

name: Potbrood
description: The dish is a bread traditionally baked in a cast-iron pot in a pit made in the ground and lined with hot coals.

name: Röggelchen
description: The dish is a small pastry in the form of a double roll made from two pieces of dough. The rye content must be at least 50% of the flour. The rye dough consists of a bread roll dough to which rye flour or sourdough is added.

name: Roti
description: The dish is a round flatbread made from stoneground whole wheat flour

name: Arsik
description: The dish is a kind of spicy fish stew, usually using common carp.

name: Gizzada
description: The dish is contained in a small, crisp pastry shell with a pinched crust and filled with a sweet and spiced coconut filling.

name: Water biscuit
description: The dish is a kind of thin, hard and brittle biscuit, and usually served with cheese or wine.

name: Taro dumpling
description: The dish is made from a thick layer of taro that has been boiled and mashed. The filling is made from seasoned ground pork. The dumpling is deep fried, and the outermost layer of taro becomes crisp, light, and fluffy.

name: Solomon Gundy
description: The dish  is made with smoked red herring and is minced and spiced with Scotch Bonnet peppers and seasonings.

name: Rum cake
description: The dish is similar to a fruitcake, with a lighter texture.

name: Bulla cake
description: The dish is a rich cake made with molasses and spiced with ginger and nutmeg, sometimes dark-colored and other times light-colored.

name: Rock cake
description: The dish is a small cake with a rough surface resembling a rock.

name: Kholodets
description: The dish is a savory gelatin made with a meat stock or broth, set in a mold to encase other ingredients.These often include pieces of meat, seafood, vegetable, or eggs.

name: Salo
description: The dish consists of salt-cured slabs of pork subcutaneous fat with or without skin and with or without layers of meat.

name: Stroganina
description: The dish consists of raw, thin, long-sliced frozen fish.

name: Zakuski
description: The dish may include cold cuts, cured fishes, mixed salads, kholodets, pirogs or pirozhki, various pickled vegetables such as beets, cucumbers, sauerkraut, pickled mushrooms, deviled eggs, hard cheeses, caviar, canapés, open sandwiches, and breads.

name: Rassolnik
description: The dish is a kind of soup made from pickled cucumbers, pearl barley, and pork or beef kidneys.

name: Solyanka
description: A thick sour soup with cabbage, salted cucumbers, meat, poultry, fish, or mushrooms

name: Dressed herring
description: A layered salad composed of diced spekesild covered with layers of grated boiled eggs, Vegetable (potatoes, carrots, beetroots), chopped onions, and mayonnaise

name: Vinegret
description: Salad dish consisted of diced cooked Vegetable (red beets, potatoes, carrots), chopped onions, as well as sauerkraut and/or brined pickles.

name: Veal Orloff
description: The dish consists of thinly sliced braised loin of veal, with duxelles and soubise layered between the slices, topped with Mornay sauce, and browned in the oven.

name: Pozharsky cutlet
description: A breaded ground chicken or veal patty

name: Korovai
description: A large round braided bread, traditionally baked from wheat flour and decorated with symbolic flags and figurines, such as suns, moons, birds, animals, and pine cones

name: Varenye
description: Whole fruit preservation made by cooking berries, other fruits, or more rarely nuts, Vegetable, or flowers, in sugar syrup (sometimes honey)

name: Pyshka
description: This dish is similar to doughnut, either ring-shaped or without a hole.

name: Angel wings
description: A traditional sweet crisp pastry made out of dough that has been shaped into thin twisted ribbons, deep-fried and sprinkled with powdered sugar.

name: Smetana
description: A dairy product produced by souring heavy cream

name: Kutia
description: This dish is a ceremonial grain dish with sweet gravy traditionally served during the Christmas – Feast of Jordan holiday season or as part of a funeral feast. The main ingredients are wheatberries, poppy seeds, honey or sugar, various nuts and sometimes raisins.

name: Guryev porridge
description: This dish is a sweet porridge prepared from semolina and milk with the addition of candied nuts (hazelnut, walnuts, almonds), honey and dried fruits (or fruit preserves).

name: Medovik
description: It is a dessert which is known for its lengthy preparation time. It consists of layers of cake with a cream filling and is often covered with nuts or crumbs made from leftover cake. While the thin layers harden shortly after coming out of the oven, the moisture of the filling softens it again over time.

name: Pastila
description: It is a small squares of pressed fruit paste or a light, airy puffs with a delicate apple flavor.

name: Pryanik
description: These sweets refer to a range of traditional sweet-baked goods and are made from flour and honey.

name: Ahriche
description: It is a dish of tripe usually consisting of ganglion, caul, lung or heart of an animal wound with intestines on a stick of oak and cooked on hot coals

name: Alloco
description: It is commonly made from cut plantains in slices, fry them until they are yellow, smash them between two plates and fry them again.

name: Bichak
description: This dish is a stuffed baked or fried pastry that comes in different forms (round, triangle, quadrangle) appetizer.

name: Waterblommetjiebredie
description: This dish is made of meat, typically lamb, stewed together with the Aponogeton distachyos flowers.

name: Chakalaka
description: This dish is usually spicy, that is traditionally served with bread, pap, samp, stews, or curries.

name: Chakhchoukha
description: This stew is made from torn or rolled pieces of cooked semolina dough that are served in a flavorful tomato-based sauce.

name: Cocada amarela
description: This dessert is made from eggs and coconut. It has a distinctive yellow colour due to the large quantity of eggs used.

name: Dabo kolo
description: This dish is a finger food consisting of small pieces of spiced fried dough. It is prepared by frying small pieces of dough cut from rolls.

name: Delele
description: This dish is prepared with baking soda and well known for its slimy texture. It can be dried before cooking, but more frequently it is cooked fresh.

name: Draw soup
description: This dish is made from okra, ogbono (Irvingia gabonensis), or ewedu leaves (jute). The name derives from the thick viscosity characteristic of the broth as it draws out of the bowl when eaten either with a spoon or, more characteristically, by dipping a small piece of solid sticky dough into it.

name: Eba
description: This dish is rich in starch and carbohydrates. It is a cooked starchy vegetable food made from dried grated cassava flour. It is often eaten with rich soups and stews, with beef, stockfish or mutton. The dish is often described as having a slightly sour, sharp taste.

name: Fesikh
description: The dish is a salted pickled fermented and dried gray mullet or whitefish.

name: Fit-fit
description: The dish is a shredded flat bread with spiced butter and jalapeno peppers.

name: Genfo
description: The dish is a stiff porridge served with dipping sauce and mixture of butter and red peppers.

name: Mugoyo
description: The dish is a sweet potates and beans.

name: Ogi
description: The dish is a maize or corn pudding soaked in water and grinded to remove husks.

name: Shark chutney
description: The dish is a boiled skinned shark, mashed and cooked with juice and lime.

name: Mala Mogodu
description: The dish is a combination of chopped tripe and intestines served with dumpling.

name: Kapana
description: The dish is a grilled meat by grilling it on an open fire.

name: Kamounia
description: The dish is a beef and liver stew prepared with cumin.

name: Hertzoggie
description: The dish is a jam-fileed tartlet or cookie commonly served on a cup pastry base.

name: Gored gored
description: The dish is a raw beef dish with cube shape.

name: Gatsby
description: The dish is a bread roll filled with chips, calamaris, seafood, and fillings with sauces.

name: Kokonte
description: The dish is a brow, grey, and deep grean stew made of dried cassava or yam.

name: Méchoui
description: The dish is a whole sheep or lamb spit-roasted on a barbecue.

name: Shahan ful
description: The dish is a slow-cooked fava beans in water, cruhed into a coarse paste.

name: Seswaa
description: The dish is made of beef or goat leftover cuts, boiled in a pot.

name: Shish taouk
description: The dish is a chicken kebab ccoked in a satay form.

name: Qatayef
description: The dish is a sweet dumpling filled with cream or nuts, or a folded pancake.

name: Spicy cow feet
description: The dish is a soup made of upper cut of cow feet with palm oil, potash, nutmegs, and seasonings.

name: Mrouzia
description: The dish is a sweet and salty meat with blend of spices of honey, cinnamon, and almonds.

name: Moambe chicken
description: The dish is a savory chicken with spices and palm butter.

name: Kuli-kuli
description: The dish is a crispy snack made from peanuts with a mixture of cassave flakes, sugar and water.

name: Koeksister
description: The dish is a confectionery made of fried dough infused in syrup or honey.

name: Kelewele
description: The dish is a fried plaintains seasoned with spices, with crisp textures.

name: Kedjenou
description: The dish is a spicy stew with a slow-cooked in a sealed pot, prepared with chicken or hen and Vegetable.

name: Iru
description: The dish is a type of fermented of processed locust bens used as a condiment in cooking.

name: Kibbeh nayyeh
description: The dish is a minced raw lamb or beef mixed with fine spices.

name: Kashk bademjan
description: The dish is made with eggplant and dairy products served as a dip and garnished with saffron, sauteed onions, garlic, and often walnuts.

name: Ageh
description: The dish is a piece of fried tofu stuffed with noodles.

name: Tihlo
description: The dish is a barley dough balls covered with meat and sauce.

name: Ghapama
description: The dish is a stuffed pumpkin stew prepared by removing the guts of the pumpkin and stuffed with boiled rice and dried fruits.

name: Sakhu sai mu
description: The dish is a tapioca balls made with starch with pork fillings.

name: Stuffed crust pizza
description: The dish is a pizza with other ingredients added into the outer edge of the crust.

name: Tufahije
description: The dish is a walnut-stuffed apples poached in sugar water.

name: Stuffed quinces
description: The dish is made from quinces stuffed with meat lamb and rice.

name: Pizza snack rolls
description: The dish is a rolled pizza consisting of bite-sized breaded pizza pockets with a fillings of tomato sauce, imitation cheese, and various pizza toppings.

name: Pavese agnolotti
description: The dish is a egg-based stuffed pasta served dry or using goose broth.

name: Casunziei
description: The dish is a stuffed pasta, consisting of filling sealed between two layers of thin pasta dough, folded in a typical half-moon shape.

name: Bánh lá
description: The dish is a leaf cake, consisting of parcel of a variety of rice stuffed with some fillings and wrapped in a leaf or leaves.

name: Bò nướng lá lốt
description: The dish is a grilled beef served on a leaf which has a spicy smell but medicinal taste.. It is commonly served in a barbecue technique.

name: Barbajuan
description: The dish is a fritter stuffed with chard, rice, cheese, and other fillings.

name: Gyeran-mari
description: The dish is made with beaten eggs mixed with several finely diced ingredients, fried and rolled.

name: Poornalu
description: The dish is a sweet and dumpling made from rice flour stuffed with jagger paste and dry fruits.

name: Pootharekulu
description: The dish is a sweet wrapped in a wafer-thin rice starch layer resembling paper and is stuffed with sugar, dry fruits, and nuts.

name: Bagel dog
description: The dish is a hot dog wrapped in bagel-style breading before or after cooking.

name: Sorullos
description: The dish is a fried cornmeal-based with stuffed cheese.

name: Chebureki
description: The dish is a fried turnovers with a filling of ground or minced meat and onions.

name: Gobi paratha
description: The dish is a flatbread stuffed with flavoured cauliflower and other vegetable.

name: Levengi
description: The dish is a fish or chicken stuffed with walnuts, onions, and various condiments, and baked in the oven.

name: Jalangkote
description: The dish is a fried dumpling stuffed with rice, vegetable, potatoes, and eggs. Spicy, sweet and sour sauce will be dipped into prior to be eaten.

name: Jalapeño popper
description: The dish are jalapeno peppers that have been hollowed out, stuffed with a mixture of cheese, spices, ground meat, and breaded and deep-fried.

name: Kalitsounia
description: The dish is a small cheese or herb snacks with different filling and serving variations.

name: Karađorđeva šnicla
description: The dish is a breaded cutlet dish with rolled veal, pork, or chicken steak, stuffed with dairy then breaded and fried.

name: Kibinai
description: The dish is a pastry filled with mutton and onion.

name: Krautshäuptchen
description: This dish is a stuffed cabbage, served with boiled potatoes and mustard sauce or bechamel sauce.

name: Szczecin pasztecik
description: This dish is a variety of pastry, a machine-produced deep-fried yeast dough stuffed with a meat or vegetarian filling, served in specialised bars as a fast food.

name: Plátanos rellenos
description: This dish consists of plantain stuffed with meat and seasonings and fried.

name: Porchetta
description: This dish is a is a savory, fatty, and moist boneless pork roast. The carcass is deboned and spitted or roasted traditionally over wood for at least eight hours, fat and skin still on.

name: Tortang talong
description: This dish is an omelette made by pan-frying grilled whole eggplants dipped in an egg mixture.

name: Buttered pineapple bun
description: This dish is a sweet bun made to resemble a pineapple with a slice of butter stuffed inside.

name: Pampushka
description: This dish is a small savoury or sweet yeast-raised bun or doughnut. Traditionally they are baked, but may also be fried. The savoury version have no filling, while the sweet version may be filled with fruits, berries, or poppy seeds, and topped with powdered sugar.

name: Stuffed racuchy
description: This dish is a type of pancake stuffed with slices of apple and served with sugar. In more modern versions, other druit can be used like bananas. There is also a savoury sweet version of this dish, filled with potatoes.

name: Rellenitos de plátano
description: This is a dish of sweet mashed plantains stuffed with a mixture of refried beans, chocolate, and cinnamon.

name: Turon
description: This dish is a snack made of thinly sliced bananas, rolled in a spring roll wrapper, fried till the wrapper is crisp and coated with caramelized brown sugar.

name: Unnakai
description: This dish is a spindle shaped sweet dessert made chiefly of banana.

name: Egg in the basket
description: This dish is an egg fried in a hole in a slice of bread.

name: Chorley cake
description: This dish is made using currants, sandwiched between two layers of unsweetened shortcrust pastry.

name: Hot Pockets
description: This dish is a brand of microwaveable turnovers generally containing one or more types of cheese, meat, or Vegetable.

name: Chicken fillet roll
description: This dish is a baguette filled with a fillet of processed chicken.

name: Galette-saucisse
description: This dish is a street food item consisting of a hot sausage, traditionally grilled, wrapped in a buckwheat crepe.

name: Kati roll
description: This street food dish is a skewer-roasted kebab wrapped in a flatbread.

name: Prawn roll
description: This dish is made using a soft white roll approximately 6 inches or 15 cm long, stuffed with a dozen or more peeled prawns, lettuce and remoulade, Thousand Island or cocktail-style sauce.

name: Popiah
description: This dish is a fresh spring roll filled with an assortment of fresh, dried, and cooked ingredients, eaten during a festival and other celebratory occasions.

name: Cachopo
description: This dish consists of two large veal fillets and includes ham and cheese, and typically has a side of french fries. It is eaten fried and hot after being breaded in eggs and breadcrumbs, and it is usually served garnished with potatoes, peppers, or mushrooms.

name: Jucy Lucy
description: This dish is a stuffed cheeseburger with the cheese inside of the meat instead of on top, resulting in a melted core of cheese.

name: Sapu Mhicha
description: This dish is made up of buffalo leaf tripe stuffed with bone marrow.

name: Tripoux
description: This dish is made with small bundles of sheep tripe, usually stuffed with sheep's feet, sweetbreads and various herbs and garden Vegetable. There are a number of variations on this dish, but they generally all involve savoury ingredients held together with sheep tripe and braised over low heat.

name: Stuffed cucumber
description: This dish is used in various cuisines around the world. The main ingredient is cucumber, which is stuffed with various fillings depending on the region. Some dishes incorporate preserved cucumbers, while others use fresh cucumbers.

name: Arctic roll
description: This dish is an ice cream cake made of vanilla ice cream wrapped in a thin layer of sponge cake to form a roll, with a layer of raspberry flavoured sauce between the sponge and the ice cream.

name: Black sesame roll
description: This dish is a refrigerated dessert. The dessert preparation starts by drying a thin layer of black sesame paste, which forms a refrigerated sheet. Once set, each sheet is rolled up individually into a sesame roll.

name: Salted Nut Roll
description: A candy bar surrounded in a layer of caramel and then covered with salted Virginia peanuts

name: Makizushi
description: This dish is generally roll-wrapped in nori (seaweed) but is occasionally wrapped in a thin omelette, soy paper, cucumber, or shiso (perilla) leaves. This dish is often cut into six or eight pieces, constituting a single roll order.

name: Minnesota sushi
description: This dish is a type of roll made by wrapping a slice of ham with cream cheese around a pickle, and then slicing it into bite-sized pieces.

name: Fruit Roll-Ups
description: This dish is a brand of snack. It is a flat, corn syrup-based, fruit-flavored snack rolled into a tube, spread on a backing sheet of cellophane to prevent the product from sticking to itself.

name: Farsu magru
description: This dish is a traditional meat roll prepared using relatively small amount of meat ingredients. It is also characterized by the way in which the lean, low-fat cuts of meat that are typically used in the dish contrast with the stuffing, which has a higher fat content.

name: Calf's liver and bacon
description: This dish is made with slices of bacon that are fried, and slices of veal liver (often covered in flour) are sauteed in the rendered fat. The bacon and slices of liver are placed in a dish and covered with a gravy made with the fond.

name: Hortobágyi palacsinta
description: This dish is a savoury crepe filled with meat (usually veal or beef). The crepes are filled with a stew, tucking in the ends.

name: Wallenbergare
description: A dish consisting of a breaded ground veal patty, flavored with cream and egg yolk, pan-fried until golden and traditionally served with potatoes, lingonberries, and peas.

name: Zürcher Geschnetzeltes
description: It is a dish made with thin slices of sautéed veal, white wine, cream, onions, and sometimes mushrooms, often served with rösti.

name: Asam pedas
description: This dish is a sour and spicy fish stew dish. It is often cooked with asam (tamarind) fruit juice with chilli and spices.

name: Balbacua
description: This dish is a beef stew made from beef, collagen-rich beef parts (oxtail, skin, and joints), and various spices cooked for several hours until very tender.

name: Flaki
description: This dish is a soup usually made with thin, cleaned strips of beef tripe.

name: Főzelék
description: This dish is a vegetable stew or soup, similar to pottage. It is simply cooked, typically by simmering, not mashing.

name: Gaisburger Marsch
description: This dish is a beef stew where the meat, cooked in a strong beef broth, is cut into cubes and served with cooked potatoes and Spätzle.

name: Galinhada
description: This dish is a stew of rice with chicken.

name: Guatita
description: This dish is a a stew whose main ingredient is pieces of tripe (cow stomach). There are various vegetarian versions of the dish in which wheat gluten is substituted for tripe.

name: Guyanese pepperpot
description: This dish is a stew that is usually reserved for special occasions because it needs to cook for several hours, and mostly eaten on Christmas Day or during the Christmas holiday season, and sometimes on Boxing Day.

name: Hamin
description: This dish is a Sabbath stew made from whole grains, cubes of meat, chickpeas or beans, onion and cumin.

name: Hochepot
description: This dish is a stew made with oxtail, shoulder of mutton, salted bacon, and vegetables. The stewed vegetables are served whole.

name: Kaldereta
description: This dish is a stew where the goat meat is stewed with vegetables and liver paste. Vegetables may include tomatoes, potatoes, olives, bell peppers, and hot peppers.

name: Kapuska
description: This dish is a cabbage stew that is known to be a dish for the poor.

name: Khoresh karafs
description: This dish is a traditional stew with celerty as the main part of the dish.

name: Kig ha farz
description: This dish is a cooked dish consisting of various meats simmered in a broth with a buckwheat flour based pudding.

name: Kuurdak
description: This dish is usually described as stewed brown meat.

name: Lancashire hotpot
description: This dish consists of lamb or mutton and onion, topped with sliced potatoes and slowly baked in a pot at a low heat.

name: Maconochie
description: The dish is a canned stew of sliced turnips, carrots, potatoes, onions, haricot beans, and beef in a thin broth.

name: Mocotó
description: The dish is made from cow's feet, stewed with beans and Vegetable.

name: Tuna pot
description: The dish is a simple dish with tuna, potatoes, onions, peppers, and tomatoes.

name: Tocană
description: The dish is a stew prepared with tomato, garlic and sweet paprika. Traditionally, it is consumed with a cornmeal mush.

name: Tharid
description: The dish is a simple meal of broth and bread, in this instance crumbled flatbread moistened with broth or stew.

name: Tatws Pum Munud
description: The dish is a traditional stew, made with smoked bacon, stock, potatoes and other Vegetable.

name: Skirts and kidneys
description: The dish is a stew made from pork and pork kidneys.

name: Saltah
description: The dish is based off a brown meat stew called maraq, a dollop of fenugreek froth, and sahawiq (a mixture of chillies, tomatoes, garlic, and herbs ground into a salsa).

name: Rössypottu
description: The dish is a stew made using potatoes (pottu, peruna), some pork and the main ingredient, so-called "rössy" i.e. blodpalt made of blood, beer, rye flour and some spices.

name: Navarin
