description: The dish is a ragoût (stew) of lamb or mutton.

name: Pottage
description: The dish is a thick soup or stew made by boiling Vegetable, grains, and, if available, meat or fish.

name: Pörkölt
description: This dish is a meat stew with boneless meat, paprika, and some vegetables.

name: Pasulj
description: This dish is a bean stew made of usually white, cranberry or pinto beans, and more rarely kidney beans. It is normally prepared with meat, particularly smoked meat such as smoked bacon, sausage, and ham hock, and is a typical winter dish.

name: Paila marina
description: This dish is a seafood soup usually served in a earthenware bowl. It usually contains a shellfish stock base cooked with different kinds of shellfish and fish.

name: Paya
description: This dish consists of the trotters (hooves) of a cow, goat, buffalo, or sheep, cooked with various spices. It is served at various festivals and gatherings, or made for special guests.

name: Butajiru
description: This dish is a soup made with pork and vegetables, flavoured with a type of fermented soybeans paste.

name: Porra antequerana
description: This dish is a thick soup consists of tomato and dried bread.

name: Fabes con almejas
description: This dish is a clam and bean stew. It is a lighter variation of other stew whose primary ingredients are sausage, beans and pork.

name: Escudella
description: The dish is a traditional Catalan meat and vegetable stew, often served with a side of pasta, rice, or both

name: Cocido montañés
description: The dish is a traditional stew from the Cantabria region in northern Spain. It is made with large white beans, chorizo, and pork, and is a hearty and filling meal.

name: Caparrones
description: The dish is a Spanish stew made of caparrón, a variety of red kidney bean, and a spicy sausage chorizo, both of which are local specialties of the Spanish La Rioja region

name: Cocido madrileño
description: The dish is a traditional chickpea-based stew associated to the Madrid region.[1] It is most popular during the winter

name: Caldo galego
description: The dish is a regional derivative (with added beans and turnip greens) of the very similar caldo verde, the traditional soup dish of neighbouring Portugal.

name: Kenchin-jiru
description: The dish is a popular Japanese vegetable soup prepared using root Vegetable and tofu prepared in various manners using myriad ingredients.

name: Hong dou tang
description: The dish is a sweet Chinese dessert made from azuki beans served in Mainland China, Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macau, and places with Chinese diaspora.

name: Zōni
description: The dish is a Japanese soup containing mochi rice cakes associated with the Japanese New Year and its tradition of osechi ceremonial foods.

name: Cup Noodles
description: The dish is a cup instant ramen developed in 1971 and manufactured by Japanese food company Nissin Foods packaged in foam, plastic, or paper cups and are prepared by adding boiling water.

name: Chankonabe
description: The dish  is a Japanese stew (a type of nabemono or one-pot dish) commonly eaten in vast quantity by sumo wrestlers as part of a weight-gain diet.

name: Dojō nabe
description: The dish is a Japanese nabemono dish cooked in a hot pot with pond loaches as it main ingridients

name: Fugu chiri
description: The dish is a pufferfish soup

name: Harihari-nabe
description: The dish is a type of nabemono made with minke whale meat and mizuna.

name: Hayashi rice
description: The dish is a popular dish in Japan as a Western-style dish, or yōshoku, that usually contains beef, onions, and button mushrooms in a thick demi-glace sauce, which often contains red wine and tomato sauce.

name: Kiritanpo
description: The dish is a Japanese freshly cooked rice pounded until somewhat mashed, then formed into cylinders around Japanese cedar skewers, and toasted over an open hearth.

name: Motsunabe
description: The dish is a type of nabemono in Japanese cuisine, which is made from beef or pork tripe or other offal

name: Shabu-shabu
description: The dish is a Japanese nabemono hotpot dish of thinly sliced meat and Vegetable boiled in water and served with dipping sauces.

name: Kagoshima ramen
description: The dish is a ramen dish which is offered in Kagoshima Prefecture, in southern Japan.

name: Hiyashi chūka
description: The dish is a Chinese-style Japanese dish consisting of chilled Chinese noodles with various toppings served in the summer.

name: Chinsukō
description: The dish is a traditional sweet often sold as a souvenir. It is a small biscuit made of mostly lard and flour, with a mild and sweet flavor similar to shortbread.

name: Coffee jelly
description: The dish is a jelly dessert flavored with coffee and sugar.

name: Hakuto jelly
description: The dish is made using the juice of ripe peaches and mineral-rich spring water. The texture is very smooth and soft, similar to the texture of the fruit itself.

name: Sata andagi
description: The dish is a sweet deep fried bun of dough similar to a doughnut. It is typically prepared so that the outside is crispy and browned while the inside is light and cake-like.

name: Tokyo Banana
description: The dish is banana-shaped sponge cake with cream filling.

name: Kakigōri
description: The dish is a shaved ice dessert flavored with syrup and a sweetener, often condensed milk.

name: Muroran curry ramen
description: The dish is a curry-flavored ramen noodle dish.

name: Amanattō
description: The dish is a traditional confectionery made of azuki or other beans, covered with refined sugar after simmering with sugar syrup and drying.

name: Raindrop cake
description: The dish is a confection made of water and agar that resembles a large raindrop.

name: Sakuramochi
description: The dish is a confection consisting of sweet, pink-colored rice cake with red bean paste filling, wrapped in a pickled cherry blossom leaf, which may or may not be eaten depending on individual preference.

name: Tokoroten
description: The dish is a gelatinous dish in Japanese cuisine, made from agarophyte seaweed.

name: Shiruko
description: The dish is a sweet porridge of red beans boiled and crushed, served in a bowl with mochi.

name: Namagashi
description: This sweet may contain fruit jellies, other gelatines, or sweetened bean paste. It is detailed, designed with using seasonal and natural motifs such as leaves and flowers to reflect the various objects of nature in four seasons.

name: Wasanbon
description: This fine-grained sugar is often used for sweets and made from thin sugarcane plants (Saccharum sinense).

name: Imagawayaki
description: This dessert is often found at festivals. The dessert is made of batter in a special pan and filled with sweet red bean paste.

name: Amezaiku
description: This candy craft artistry is sculpted of multi-coloured sweetener that is clear, thick, and sticky made by converting starch to sugars.

name: Anmitsu
description: This dessert is made of small cubes of agar jelly, a white translucent jelly made from red algae. It is served in a bowl with sweet red bean paste, boiled peas, and a variety of fruits such as peach slices, oranges, pieces of pineapples, and/or cherries

name: Arare
description: This snack is a type of bite-sized cracker made from glutinous rice and flavored with soy sauce.

name: Botamochi
description: This confection is made with glutinous rice and white rice with ratio of 7:3, or only glutinous rice, plus sweet red bean paste.

name: Beika
description: The name refers to a dry confectionery that is made out of rice.

name: Chitose ame
description: This candy is given to children on the festival that celebrates the passage of their children into middle childhood. This candy is long, thin, red and white candy, and is wrapped in a thin, clear, and edible rice paper film that resembles plastic. This candy is usually given with a bag decorated with a crane and a turtle.

name: Daifuku
description: This confection is a small round rice cake stuffed with a sweet filling, most commonly a sweetened red bean paste. It is often served along with a green tea.

name: Yōkan
description: The dish is made of red bean paste, agar, and sugar. It is usually sold in a block form, and eaten in slices.

name: Monaka
description: The dish consists of red bean paste sandwiched between two thin, crisp wafers made from rice cake. The wafers can be square, triangle, or complicated shapes such as cultural landmarks or symbols. The dish is a type of dessert served with tea.

name: Hanabiramochi
description: This dessert is usually eaten at the beginning of the year. The exact shape of the dish is strictly defined by tradition. The white rice cake covering is flat and round, folded over to form a semicircular shape, and must have a pink colour showing through in the centre of the confection, fading to a white at the edge.

name: Higashi
description: The dish recipe is one or more kinds of sugar, with a particular sort of flour and some other additives, while there is some variants made solely of sugar, with no flour content.

name: Hishi mochi
description: The sweet is diamond-shaped and typically formed from three layers of red (pink), white, and green rice cake, from top to bottom. Depending on the region, red may be substituted for yellow, or the sweet may have five or seven layers instead. It is usually presented with traditional dolls.

name: Karintō
description: This is a sweet, deep-fried snack. It is made primarily of flour, yeast, and brown sugar. It has a deep brown and pitted appearance and takes the form of a bite-sized pillow or short cylinder.

name: Konpeitō
description: It takes the form of a small sphere with a bumpy surface, and comes in a variety of colors and flavors.

name: Kusa mochi
description: It is made from rice cake and leaves of mugwort. The leaves are kneaded into the mochi, giving it a vivid green colour. The greenness depends on the amount of mugwort blended in the mochi.

name: Kuzumochi
description: A dessert that can be either mochi cake made from kudzu powder, starch derived from the root of the kudzu plant, or rice cakes made from Lactobacillales-fermented wheat starch. The usual preparation consists in combining kudzu powder with water and sugar, and cooking it over a gentle heat, stirring continuously until the mixture thickens and becomes transparent. This process also imparts an elastic texture to the kudzu. The transparent appearance of the final product contributes to a cool sensation, making it a popular choice for consumption during warmer months.

name: Momiji manjū
description: A buckwheat and rice cake shaped like a maple leaf, and it is typically filled with red bean paste.

name: Kamameshi
description: A rice dish traditionally cooked in an iron pot. Many varieties exist, but most consist of rice seasoned with soy sauce or mirin, and cooked with meats and vegetables.

name: Katemeshi
description: Typical ingredients in the preparation of this dish included rice, barley, millet, chopped daikon radish root and leaves, and other greens. The use of daikon in the dish was very common. Other ingredients used in the dish, when available, included wheat, carrots, turnips, burdock, taro, pumpkin, soybeans, mushrooms, kidney beans, and adzuki beans, among others.

name: Red bean rice
description: Rice dish consisting of rice cooked with red beans.

name: Tenmusu
description: Rice ball wrapped with nori that is filled with deep-fried tempura shrimp.

name: Nanakusa-no-sekku
description: Seven-herb rice porridge consisting of Japanese parsley, sheperd's purse, cudweed, chickweed, nipplewort, turnip, and radish.

name: Tekkadon
description: Rice dish topped with thin-sliced raw tuna. The spicy version is made with what can be a mix of spicy ingredients, a spicy orange sauce, or both, usually incorporating spring onions.

name: Tendon
description: Fried shrimp on a bowl of rice.

name: Unadon
description: Typically served in a large bowl filled with steamed white rice, and topped with fillets of eel grilled. The fillets are glazed with a sweetened soy-based sauce, called tare and caramelized, preferably over charcoal fire. The fillets are not flayed, and the grayish skin side is placed faced down.

name: Wappameshi
description: Rice dish in special round containers seasoned with lightly-salted dashi broth, topped with steamed seasonal seafood.

name: Chirashizushi
description: The dish serves the rice in a bowl and tops it with a variety of raw fish and vegetable garnishes. The dish"s name has the meaning of "scattered sushi".

name: Oshizushi
description: The chef lines the bottom a block-shaped mold with the toppings(cooked fish or cured fish), covers them with sushi rice, and then presses the mold's lid to create a compact block. The block is removed from the mold and then cut into bite-sized pieces

name: Katsu-sando
description: This dish is a sandwich which made of deep-fried pork cutlet between slices of bread.

name: Yakisoba-pan
description: This dish consists of fried wheat noodles that is sandwiched between a white bread roll bun.

name: Kaki furai
description: The dish consisting of panko-breaded deep-fried oysters

name: Kakiage
description: The dish is made by batter-dipping and deep-frying a batch of ingredients such as shrimp bits  It may use other seafood such as small scallops, shredded vegetables or a combination of such ingredients.

name: Dovga
description: soup made from plain yoghurt and herbs. The soup ingredients can vary seasonally and regionally, the soup usually includes coriander, dill, mint, and spinach.

name: Joshpara
description: made of unleavened wheat dough squares filled with ground meat and condiments.

name: Piti
description: It is made with mutton and vegetables (tomatoes, potatoes, chickpeas), infused with saffron water to add flavour and colour, all covered by a lump of fat, and cooked in a sealed crock

name: Khash
description: This dish consists of boiled cow or sheep parts, which might include the head, feet, and stomach (tripe).

name: Water chestnut cake
description: This dish is a sweet dim sum made of water chestnut.

name: Chicken feet
description: This dish is a part of chicken which cooked and eaten in many countries. This dish has a distinct gelatinous texture different from the rest of the chicken meat.

name: Tong sui
description: The dish is a collective term for any sweet soup served as a dessert typically at the end of a meal.

name: Belgian bun
description: The dish is a sweet bun containing sultanas and usually topped with fondant icing and half a glace cherry. Some recipes also include lemon curd. The bun is round or square shaped, with rounded off edges

name: Buñuelo
description: The dish is a fried dough fritter. They typically consist of a simple, wheat-based yeast dough, often flavored with anise, that is thinly rolled, cut or shaped into individual pieces, then fried and finished off with a sweet topping. It may be filled with a variety of things, sweet or savory. They can be round in ball shapes or disc-shaped.

name: Finger bun
description: The dish is a fruit bun. At one time it was a bakery and school staple but its popularity has waned.

name: Fruit bun
description: The dish is a type of sweet roll made with fruit, fruit peel, spices and sometimes nuts. They are made with fruit and fruit peel , which are sprinkled and cooked with sugar nibs.

name: Tuna bun
description: The dish is a bun that contains tuna paste.

name: Ham and egg bun
description: The dish is a bun or bread that contains a sheet of egg and ham.

name: Pork chop bun
description: The dish consists of a bun which is extremely crisp outside and very soft inside. A fried pork chop is filled into the bun horizontally.

name: Manchet
description: The dish is a wheaten, yeast-leavened bread of very good quality, or a small flat circular loaf. It was a bread that was small enough to be held in the hand.

name: Pineapple bun
description: The dish is a kind of sweet bun. Despite the name, it does not traditionally contain pineapple; rather, the name refers to the look of the characteristic topping (which resembles the texture of a pineapple).

name: Christmas ham
description: The dish is a ham often served for special occassion dinner.

name: Ham and eggs
description: The dish is a dish combining various preparations of ham and egg.

name: Jambon-beurre
description: The dish is a ham sandwich made of a fresh baguette sliced open, spread with butter (salted or unsalted) and filled with slices of ham.

name: Bunny chow
description: The dish consisting of a hollowed-out loaf of white bread filled with curry and a serving of salad on the side.

name: Schnitz un knepp
description: The dish consists of ham or pork shoulder with dried apples and dumplings.

name: Toast Hawaii
description: The dish is an open sandwich consisting of a slice of toast with ham and cheese, and a maraschino cherry in the middle of a pineapple slice, baked so that the cheese starts to melt.

name: Crispy pata
description: The dish consists of deep fried pig trotters or knuckles served with a soy-vinegar dip.

name: Akashiyaki
description: The dish is a small round dumpling. The dumpling is made of an egg-rich batter and octopus dipped into a thin fish broth before eating.

name: Aletria
description: The dish is a custardy dessert based on thin like pasta.

name: Balut
description: The dish is a fertilized developing egg embryo that is boiled or steamed and eaten from the shell.

name: Coddled egg
description: The dish refers to eggs that have been cracked into a ramekin or another small container, placed in a water bath or bain-marie and gently or lightly cooked just below boiling temperature. They can be partially cooked, mostly cooked, or hardly cooked at all

name: Telur gulung
description: The dish is a food in which an egg is fried and then rolled using a skewer which is usually made of bamboo.

name: Iron egg
description: The dish consists of small eggs that have been repeatedly stewed in a mix of spices and air-dried. The resulting eggs are dark brown on the outside, chewy in texture, and very flavourful compared to standard boiled eggs.

name: Eggs and brains
description: The dish consists of pork brains (or those of another mammal) and scrambled eggs.

name: Haminados
description: The dish consists of eggs that are cooked for a long time, resulting in red-brown whites and darkened yolks.

name: Hangtown fry
description: The most common version of the dish includes bacon and oysters combined with eggs, and fried together.

name: Masala omelette
description: The dish is a variant of the omelette. Its main ingredients are eggs, herbs, tomatoes and spices that vary by region.

name: Silog
description: The dish is a class of breakfast dishes containing fried rice and fried egg. They are served with various side dish, often fried as well, and usually meat dishes such as tapa, longganisa or ham.

name: Chhurpi
description: This is a dairy product made from buttermilk, which is boiled, and the solid mass is separated from the liquid and drained in a cloth. The resulting soft, white product resembles ricotta and has a neutral taste, often fermented for a tangy flavor. To make the hard variety, the soft chhurpi is pressed in a jute bag to remove excess water, dried, cut into cubes, and hung over fire to further harden.

name: Sha phaley
description: The dish consists of bread stuffed with seasoned meat and cabbage, which is then fashioned into semi-circular or circular shapes and which according to regional variations is either deep fried or pan fried like pot stickers.

name: Sinki
description: This dish is a preserved fermented vegetable made from radish tap roots. To prepare the dish, aged radish slivers are pressed into a hole lined with bamboo and straw, covered with vegetation, rocks, wood, and mud, and then allowed to cure for about a month. After curing, the preserved radish is sun-dried and can be stored for several years.

name: Gundruk
description: The dish is obtained from the fermentation of leafy vegetables sometimes mixed with the roots as well. It is served as a side dish with the main meal and is also used as an appetizer.

name: Dhindo
description: This dish is made by gradually adding flour to boiling water while stirring, typically using buckwheat or millet flour. It is served with various accompaniments, such as lentils, curries, and condiments, and is eaten by forming small balls and dipping them into soups or liquids.

name: Bap
description: This dish is a term for cooked rice made by boiling rice or other grains, such as black rice, barley, sorghum, millets, and beans, until the water is absorbed. Various ingredients like vegetables, seafood, and meat can be added to create different variants of this dish.

name: Wandouhuang
description: This is a light and refreshing paste-like cake made from yellow peas or yellow pea flour, water, and sugar, with a slightly sweet taste. Traditionally associated with spring.

name: Tomato omelette
description: This is a vegan breakfast dish, made primarily from chickpea flour or batter with added tomatoes, onions, and green chillies. The batter is cooked on a skillet until golden and is typically served hot with condiments.

name: Tavče gravče
description: This dish is made with fresh beans, often served baked in an unglazed earthenware pot.

name: Ragda pattice
description: The dish is made of mashed potato patties and pea sauce.

name: Peabutter
description: This is a savory spread used as an alternative to peanut butter.

name: Red bean cake
description: This is a cake with a sweet red bean paste filling.

name: Fasole cu cârnați
description: This dish is a baked beans and sausages, often added with smoked pork, carrots, onions, tomatoes, parsnip, tomato sauce and bay leaf.

name: Matevž
description: This dish is a beans and potatoes dish, usually eaten with pickled cabbage or turnips.

name: Pie floater
description: This dish commonly consists of a traditional meat pie, usually sitting, but sometimes submerged (traditionally upside down) in a bowl of thick pea soup made from blue boiler peas.

name: Msabbaha
description: This dish is a variation of hummus made up of whole garbanzo beans and tahini.

name: Chhena Matar Tarkari
description: It is a vegetarian dish. It generally consists of peas and acid-set cheese in a tomato-based sauce, spiced with garam masala.

name: Grey peas
description: This dish is usually a snack served on a plate, sprinkled with salt, mixed with cracklings and onions. Soak the peas and cook them gently (it is important not to overcook so that the peas do not come out of their skin). Chopped bacon and onions are fried in a pan.

name: Githeri
description: This is a meal consisting of maize and legumes (primarily beans) mixed and boiled together. The maize and beans are mixed in a type of pot, with water added, and the mixture is boiled until fully cooked.

name: Douzhi
description: It is similar to soy milk, but made from mung beans. It is generally slightly sour, with an rotten egg-like smell.

name: Dilly beans
description: The dish preserves this summer legume. Often flavoured with dill, it may contain garlic, Tabasco sauce, and red pepper. Best kept in glass jars for safekeeping over the winter months, it can be served on its own as a snack, alongside a main dish, or in salad.

name: Dalcha
description: Primary ingredients are lentils, can be chick pea or sometimes pigeon pea. Vegetables or meats, both chicken or mutton, may also be added to the stew.

name: Ciceri e tria
description: The dish is prepared with pasta and chickpeas as primary ingredients and includes fried pasta. Some versions of the dish may have a significant amount of broth, which may be eaten using a spoon. Some of the pasta (from one-third to one-half) is fried in oil as part of its preparation, while the rest of it is boiled.

name: Bob chorba
description: This dish is made from dry beans, onions, tomatoes, spearmint and carrots.

name: Bouneschlupp
description: This dish a green bean soup with potatoes, bacon, and onions.

name: Medisterpølse
description: This specialty food consist of a thick spiced sausage made of minced pork and lard, stuffed into a casing.

name: Bondiola sandwich
description: This dish is a sandwich made with thick slices of pork shoulder. The meat consists of slices of roasted or cured pork shoulder and it is usually served on crispy brioche bread. It can be topped with a variety of condiments and vegetables.

name: Käsekrainer
description: This dish is a type of lightly smoked sausages containing roughly torn bits of pork and 10% to 20% cheese (for example Emmentaler) cut into small cubes.

name: Cervelat
description: This dish is a sausage produced in Switzerland, France, Belgium, the Netherlands, and parts of Germany. The recipe and preparation of the sausage vary regionally.

name: Salchichón
description: This dish is a summer sausage that is made by smoking, drying, cooking, or some combination. It is made with pork, although some recipes use other meats including ox, veal, or horse.

name: Lukanka
description: This dish is semi-dried, has a flattened cylindrical shape, and brownish-red interior in a skin that is normally covered with a white fungus. The mix of small pieces of meat and fat give the interior a grainy structure.

name: Botifarra
description: This dish is based on ancient recipes, either the Roman sausage botulu or the lucanica, made of raw pork and spices, with variants today in Italy and in the Portuguese and Brazilian linguiça

name: Nem chua
description: This dish is a fermented pork dish. It is mainly composed of a mixture of lean pork and thin strips of cooked rind, garnished with garlic and chilli.

name: Sibiu Salami
description: The dish is a salami made with pork meat, pork fat, salt and condiments, fermented and air-dried.

name: Botillo
description: This is a dish of meat-stuffed pork intestine. It is a is a meat product made from different pieces left over from the butchering of a pig, including the ribs, tail, and bones with a little meat left on them.

name: Naem
description: This dish is a pork sausage. It is a fermented food with a sour flavour. It has a short shelf life and is often eaten in raw form after fermentation. It is used as an ingredient in various dishes and is also served as a side dish.

name: Qazı
description: This is a traditional sausage-like food made from horse meat. It is a common element on a festive meal table. A reviewer described the dish as smoky and earthy. It is often eaten cold, sometimes sliced, and served as an appetiser.

name: Jingisukan
description: The dish is a grilled mutton dish prepared on a convex metal skillet or other grill. It is often cooked alongside beansprouts, onions, mushrooms, and bell peppers, and served with a sauce based in either soy sauce or sake.

name: Tokushima Ramen
description: The dish is a pork broth ramen that is seasoned with soy-sauce, and has topping of thinly sliced pork belly, bamboo shoots, green onions, bean sprouts, and raw eggs.

name: Qarta
description: The dishes are boiled and pan-fried horse rectum, taken from the final few inches of the digestive tract before the muscular part of the anus. It is served without sauce or spices. It is prepared in various ways to clean it thoroughly and remove any unpleasant taste due to the provenance of the tissue.

name: Sundae sausage
description: The sausage dish is generally made by steaming cow or pig's intestines stuffed with various ingredients.

name: Yudoufu
description: This hot pot dish is tofu simmered in a kombu stock and served with ponzu and various condiments.

name: Burro percherón
description: This dish is a variation of classic burrito, which traditionally prepared with grilled or charcoal-roasted meat, avocado, cheese, and tomatoes (although variants exist in each restaurant).

name: Sai ua
description: This is minced pork meat, herbs, spices, and red curry paste.

name: Prawn cocktail
description: The dish consists of shelled, cooked prawns in a seafood sauce or cocktail sauce served in a glass.

name: Curtido
description: The food is usually made with cabbage, onions, carrots, oregano, and sometimes lime juice.

name: Escamol
description: This is food known as insect caviar. They are made are from the edible larvae and pupae of ants

name: Kishka
description: The dish refers to various types of sausage or stuffed intestine with a filling made from a combination of meat and meal, often grain or potato.

name: Liverwurst
description: This is a sausage made from liver. Many varieties are spread. It usually contains pigs" or calves" liver. Other ingredients are meat (notably veal), fat, and spices

name: Lincolnshire sausage
description: The sausage dish is made with coarsely chopped or ground pork mixed with binders, seasonings and preservative.

name: Doctor's sausage
description: This sausage dish is a emulsified boiled sausage with pale pink color and low fat content.

name: Oxford sausage
description: The modern version is considered, typically, to consist of a mixture of pork and veal, seasoned with lemon and herbs.

name: Lorne sausage
description: This sausage dish is a traditional food item made from minced meat, rusk and spices.

name: Bhakkha
description: A fluffy rice cake served in breakfast or as a snack with freshly prepared tomato pickle.

name: South Asian pickle
description: It is a pickled food made from a variety of vegetables, meats and fruits preserved in brine, vinegar, edible oils, and various spices.

name: Romeritos
description: A dish consisting of tender sprigs of seepweed which are boiled and served in sauce seasoned with shrimp jerky blended into the mix. Typical additional ingredients include boiled potatoes and re-hydrated shrimp.

name: Bagiya
description: It is a steamed dumpling that consists of an external covering of rice flour and an inner content of sweet substances such like vegetables and other fried items.

name: Battered sausage
description: They are made up of a pork sausage dipped in batter and usually served with chips.

name: Tripas
description: They are the small intestines of farm animals that have been cleaned, boiled and grilled.

name: Totopo
description: The food is a flat, round, or triangular corn item similar to a tortilla, that has been toasted, fried or baked.

name: Cabrito
description: This food is roast whole goat over a charcoal fire.

name: Poc chuc
description: This is a dish of meat, commonly pork, that is prepared in citrus marinade and cooked over a grill.

name: Pollo a la brasa
description: This dish is a variety of rotisserie chicken. It originally consists of a chicken (cooked on a spit over charcoal and seasoned only with salt) served with large french fries, though today additional spices are used to prepare it. It is almost always served with creamy (mayonnaise-based) sauces.

name: Pollo motuleño
description: This dish consists of chicken cooked with orange juice, achiote, and plantains.

name: Puntas
description: This dish consists of small cuts of meat cooked in various sauces, either of dried chili or fresh chilis sauces. Initially, the tips were made with strips of leftover beef cut. Then, different types of meat have been used.

name: Arroz poblano
description: This dish is made with rice and gets its green color from a type of pepper that is processed into a liquid.

name: Fried ice cream
description: This dish is a dessert made of a scoop of ice cream that is frozen hard, then breaded or coated in a batter before being quickly deep-fried, creating a warm, crispy shell around the still-cold ice cream.

name: Caldo de siete mares
description: This dish is a fish soup typically made with tomato, fish, or seafood broth with local fresh seafood ingredients and cooked quickly in a thin broth.

name: Calavera
description: This dish is an edible decorative skulls made from sugar.

name: Cochinito de piloncillo
description: This dish is a sweet bread made with a type of sweetener made from sugar cane.

name: Manjar blanco
description: This dish consists of a sweet, white spread or pastry filling made with milk.

name: Nicuatole
description: This dish is a gelatinous dessert made from ground maize and sugar.

name: Wensleydale cheese
description: This is a medium cheese that is supple and crumbly. It has a slight honey aroma.

name: Sulguni
description: This is a type of cheese that has a sour, moderately salty flavor, a dimpled texture, and an elastic consistency.

name: Brési
description: The dish is a dried and smoked beef.

name: Bündnerfleisch
description: The dish is an air-dried meat, usually beef.

name: Lutefisk
description: The dish is dried whitefish, usually cod, made from aged fish.

name: Katsuobushi
description: The dish is a simmered, smoked, and fermented skipjack tuna.

name: Kipper
description: This dish is a whole herring, a small, oily fish, that has been split in a butterfly fashion from tail to head along the dorsal ridge, gutted, salted or pickled, and cold-smoked over smouldering wood chips

name: Açaí na tigela
description: The dish is made from frozen and mashed fruit of the acai palm with creamy texture.

name: Cajuzinho
description: The dish is made of peanuts, cashew nuts, and sugar, shaped like a tiny cashew.

name: Creme de papaya
description: The dish is a papaya blended with vanilla ice cream.

name: Mané pelado
description: The dish is a cake made from shredded yuca and coconat, and a salted cheese.

name: Maria-mole
description: The dish is similar shape to marshmallow, made with sugar, gelatine, egg whites.

name: Olho de sogra
description: The dish is a candy made of dried plum with crystal sugar.

name: Pavê
description: The dish is an alternating layer of biscuits and a cream made with condensed milk.

name: Pé de moleque
description: The dish is a candy made of peanuts and molasses.

name: Čvarci
description: The dish a variant of pork rinds. They are a kind of pork cracklings, with fat thermally extracted from the lard. Preparation involves melting the lard.

name: Brudet
description: The dish is a fish stew with spices, Vegetable and red or white wine, and vinegar.

name: Kotlovina
description: The dish is a stewed meat dish and sausages stewed in their own juice with onions, potatoes, tomatoes, bell peppers, and paprika.

name: Meso 'z tiblice
description: The dish is a salty meat made with rubbing garlic, salt, in a wodden containers.

name: Fisherman's soup
description: The dish is a spicy paprika based fish soup with bright red color.

name: Međimurska gibanica
description: The dish is a layered cake made from filo pastry, cheese, poppy seeds, and apples.

name: Frittella
description: The dish is made from dough with raisins, orange peel, and lemon peel on them with fillings.

name: Grahova pretepena juha
description: The dish is a thick bean soup with milk and cream, called white bean soup.

name: Pašticada
description: The dish is a braised beef cooked in a sweet and sour dark sauce.

name: Krofne
description: The dish is an airy filled doughnuts made with jelly, marmalade, jam, or chocolate with cinnamon.

name: Areias
description: The dish is a biscuit coated with sugar and cinnamon, which resemble sand.

name: Bacalhau à Brás
description: The dish is a shredded salted cod chopped with fried potatoes, cooked with eggs.

name: Tripas à moda do Porto
description: The dish is a beef stomach with white beans, carrots, and rice.

name: Broa de Avintes
description: The dish is a dark brown, dense bread, made with maize and rye flours.

name: Folar
description: The dish is a bread with melted sugar and cinammon.

name: Queijo de Azeitão
description: The dish is a simple cheese made from sheep milk.

name: Pão de Mafra
description: The dish is a staple bread commonly eaten with butter or jam, hams or cheeses.

name: Rojões
description: The dish is a fried pork with clams.

name: Bife a cavalo
description: The dish consists of grilled or pan-fried steak with rice, beans, and salad.

name: Xarém
description: The dish is a thick soup made with corn, clams, sardines, and grilled meats.

name: Cozido à portuguesa
description: The dish is a mixed meal consisting of Vegetable, meat, and other toppings.

name: Cebolada
description: The dish is a onion stew, sauce, or paste.

name: Lokma
description: The dish is a dessert made of leavened and deep fried dough balls, soaked in syrup or honey, sometimes coated with cinnamon or other ingredients.

name: Akkawi
description: It is a white brine cheese, commonly made with pasteurized cow's milk, but can also be made with goat or sheepmilk. It is commonly used as a table cheese eaten by itself or paired with fruit.

name: Sopa de cacahuete
description: The dish is a soup made from peanuts, often with various other ingredients

name: Kilishi
description: It is a form of dried meat, typically made with beef, Lamb and mutton or goat.

name: Mechouia salad
description: This dish is a grilled vegetable, tomatoes, peppers, onions and garlic salad, that may also contain eggplant.

name: Laffa
description: The dish is s a large, thin flatbread with that is traditionally vegan and cooked in an oven. It is most often used to wrap falafel, kebab, and shawarma to make sandwiches, to dip in hummus, matbucha and other dips, or with shakshouka, and other dishes.

name: Malewa
description: The dish is a smoked bamboo shoot.

name: Apio
description: The dish is an appetizer which is made from celeriac and carrot and served cold.

name: Krembo
description: The dish is a chocolate-coated marshmallow treat that consists of a round biscuit base, topped with fluffy marshmallow creme-like foam, coated in a thin layer of sweet baking chocolate, and wrapped in colourful, thin aluminum foil.

name: Chipsi mayai
description: The dish is a simple potato-egg omelette.

name: Hutspot
description: The dish is boiled and mashed potatoes, carrots, and onions.

name: Chai tow kway
description: The dish is stir-fried cubes of radish cake.

name: Cezerye
description: A semi-gelatinous dessert made from caramelised carrots, shredded coconut, and roasted walnuts, hazelnuts, or pistachios.

name: Porkkanalaatikko
description: A dish are mashed carrots, mixed with boiled rice or barley, and liquid.

name: Tzfatit
description: A semi-hard salty cheese, originally from sheep's milk. The milk is pasteurized at a low 72 °C (162 °F), which preserves the food proteins. Trimming is based largely on the action of enzymes contained in a special ferment and on calcium chloride rather than on the action of lactic acid. The fermentation is quick, about an hour. After the separation of most of the whey, the cheese is stored for several hours in straw or plastic baskets to drain the remaining whey and to form its round shape. For the remainder of the draining time, the cheese is inverted several times to help the draining and to form the basket's pattern on all sides.

name: Carrot chip
description: carrots that have been fried or dehydrated

name: Rujak shanghai
description: boiled sliced gurita (octopus) as well as edible jellyfish, kangkung, and served with thick red sweet and sour sauce, mixed with pineapple juice, and toasted crushed peanuts

name: Ayam buah keluak
description: dish consisting of chicken (ayam), tamarind gravy and keluak nuts

name: Pie tee
description: A thin and crispy pastry tart shell often filled with a spicy, shredded Chinese turnips, sweet mixture of thinly sliced vegetables and prawns

name: Bakwan
description: beansprouts, shredded cabbages and carrots, battered and deep fried in cooking oil

name: Sekoteng
description: a ginger-based hot drink which includes peanuts, diced bread, and tapioca pearls (known locally as pacar cina)

name: Guazi
description: baked seeds of the sunflower, pumpkin, or watermelon seeds

name: Youtiao
description: This dish is a long golden-brown deep-fried strip of wheat flour dough

name: Grass jelly
description: The jelly is made by boiling the aged and slightly oxidized stalks and leaves of Platostoma palustre (Mesona chinensis) with potassium carbonate and a little starch for several hours, then let it cool and served with sweet beverages.

name: Yusheng
description: This dish consists of strips of raw fish (sometimes salmon), mixed with shredded Vegetable and a variety of sauces and condiments, among other ingredients

name: Albaloo polo
description: The dish is made with rice and sour cherries usually served with chicken, koobideh, or other types of kebab as well as some form of stews.

name: Kateh
description: The dish is sticky rice dish and speed of cooking makes it popular for casual dinners.

name: Seenakku
description: The dish is a popular sweet, and is served with grated coconut.

name: Puffed rice cakes
description: The dish is a flat hard food made with puffed rice. Typically, it is eaten as a snack or used as a base for other ingredients.

name: Shir Berenj
description: The dish is a rice pudding flavored with rose water, spices such as cinnamon or cardamom, and often containing almonds. It may be served warm or chilled as a dessert.

name: bakabana
description: The dish is a type of fried banana.

name: Huai'an Pingqiao tofu
description: The dish is a mixed tofu with seafood, mushrooms, and chicken with soft textures.

name: Kwacoco
description: The dish consisting in pureed cocoyam wrapped and steamed in banana leaves.

name: Dombolo
description: The dish is a steamed bread. It is a popular staple food. The bread is prepared in a container in a pot of boiling water.

name: Galletas pesquera
description: The dish is characteristically very thin and disc-shaped, usually with three or more small perforations.

name: Picnic biscuit
description: The dish is a type of small, rectangular biscuit.

name: Beaver Tail
description: The dish referred to quick-baked dough "especially in early 19th-century places where people might camp for one night and where there was no frying pan." It is a fried dough pastry that is specially hand-stretched into the shape of a beaver's tail.

name: Chasan
description: The dish is golden brown and crispy. It is made by rolled wirelike strips. Usually, It has a variety of shapes. It is a kind of afternoon tea snack and that is why it is so named.

name: Hellimli
description: The dish is a savoury pastry made with halloumi cheese.

name: Hot water crust pastry
description: The dish is a type of pastry used for savoury pies. It is traditionally used for producing hand-made pies. The pastry is made by heating water, melting the fat in it, bringing the mixture to a boil, and finally incorporating the flour. This can be done by beating the flour into the mixture in the pan, or by kneading on a pastry board. Either way, the result is a hot and rather sticky paste that can be used for hand-raising: shaping by hand, sometimes using a dish or bowl as an inner mould. The moulded crust retains its shape as it cools, and is prepared for baking with a filling and additional layer of pastry crust on top. Hand-raised does not produce a neat and uniform finish, as there will be sagging during the cooking of the filled pie. This is generally accepted as the mark of a hand-made pie. It is possible, however, to bake the pastry in a mould, as with other pies.

name: Huff paste
description: The dish is a stiff pie shell made using a mixture of flour, suet, and boiling water. The pastry when cooked creates a tough protective layer around the food inside. When cooked, the pastry is generally discarded as it is virtually inedible. However, the shell becomes soaked with the meat juices and historically was sometimes eaten by house servants after the meal had concluded. Its main purpose is simply to create a solid container for the pie's ingredients. The flour itself is stronger than normal flour, often made from coarsely ground rye, and suet, which is mixed with hot water.

name: Malsouka
description: The dish is a pastry sheet. It is created by spreading wafer-thin layers of batter on a heated pan rather than by rolling a raw dough.

name: Mantecada
description: The dish is spongy pastry, baked in square or rectangular box-shaped paper instead of in the typical muffin round paper cups. The pastry leaves a characteristic cross-shaped silhouette on the paper when it is removed.

name: Pastry heart
description: The dish is a regional dessert item. The dish is a heart shaped flaky puff pastry, similar to a pastry in a palm leaf shape or a butterfly shape or palm leaves pastry, that is usually topped with a white sugar icing that has a hard shell but is soft on the inside.

name: Yurla
description: The dish is a wheat pastry with butter.

name: Chestnut pie
description: A pie prepared with chestnuts as a primary ingredient.Shelled whole or chopped chestnuts may be used, which may be boiled or roasted. A chestnut purée may also be used.

name: Flipper pie
description: A meat pie made from harp seal flippers, cooked with Vegetable in a thick sauce and then covered with pastry.

name: Lanttusupikas
description: A double-folded buttered flaky crust pie, filled with thin, braised swede slices and pork loin.

name: Wagafi bread
description: A type of bread that normally contains a greater amount of flour than normal bread. It is a flat, thin bread. The bread is made in a hole based on local tradition.

name: Ttongppang
description: It is bread filled with red bean paste and walnut bits that is shaped like stylized human feces.

name: Canadian white bread
description: Bread made from wheat or white flour. It usually has a protein content of 12 or 13%.

name: Cholermus
description: It is a kind of pancake, or "shredded", "fried crepe", that is typically eaten for supper.

name: Khubz
description: The dish is the usual word for bread.

name: Kisra
description: The dish is a popular thin fermented bread.

name: Palianytsia
description: The dish is a bread that has a semi-circular cut across the top third of the loaf.

name: Ngome
description: The dish is a flatbread using only millet, water and vegetable oil.

name: Pambazo
description: The dish is a bread with golden and crispy in its outer layer and white and very light in its inner part.

name: Grater cake
description: The dish is a dessert of grated coconut in a fondant of sugar.

name: Asham
description: The dish is made by shelling dry corn, parching it, and then grinding it finely.

name: Red Peas Soup
description: The dish is a soup made of kidney beans, seasonings such as scotch bonnet pepper, pimento seeds, etc. Traditionally, the broth includes a pigtail.

name: Cocktion
description: The dish is made from parched corn and sugar rolled into balls and sometimes colored.

name: Fio Fio
description: The dish is a soup made of guinea pea and cocoyam.

name: Funkaso
description: The dish is a savoury fried dumpling made with wheat and eaten with soup, honey, or sugar.

name: Marghi special
description: The dish is a soup made of fish with spinach, tomatoes, bean sprouts, and tamarind broth.

name: Isidudu
description: The dish is a porridge made from ground corn.

name: Harqma
description: The dish is a soup or stew prepared using lamb.

name: Tibs
description: The dish is a sauteed vegetable with meat, served in hot to mild temperatures.

name: Chaudin
description: The dish is a sausage-like variant made from ingredients sewn up in a pig's stomach, cooked with spices, and rice.

name: Stuffed mallow
description: The dish is a mallow leaves, stuffed with meat lamb or rice.

name: Stuffed melon
description: The dish is a melon stuffed with meat lamb and rice.

name: Occhi di lupo
description: The dish is a large-sized, tubular stuffed pasta, served with a stuffing or filling.

name: Ayam pansuh
description: The dish is a cooked chicken meat in a bamboo stalk, filled with water, seasonings, and covered with tapioca leaves from the cassave plan.

name: Ladera
description: This is a category of vegetable dishes cooked in olive oil.

name: Scovardă
description: This dish is a type of stuffed pastry. The dough is folded around the stuffing which usually consists of different types of cheese.

name: Carpetbag steak
description: This dish consists of an end cut of steak, such as scotch fillet or eye fillet. A pocket is cut in the meat via a small entry cut and then expanded internally, into which oysters are stuffed, and the opening closed with toothpicks or thread.

name: Eggplant papoutsaki
description: This dish consists of eggplants which have been boiled or roasted and the tops cut off lengthwise, which is why they resemble little shoes.

name: Stuffed sorrel
description: This dish is made of sorrel leaves stuffed with meat (lamb) and rice, or more rarely rice only.

name: Zoervleis
description: This dish is a regional meat dish traditionally made with horse meat, but nowadays beef is commonly used. The meat is marinated in vinegar and often accompanied by french fries.

name: Alicot
description: This dish is a stew made of the cheapest parts of poultry, slowly simmered.

name: Kadyos, baboy, kag langka
description: This dish is a pork soup or stew with pigeon peas, pork, and jackfruit used as the three main ingredients. The soup is also traditionally soured with batuan fruits.

name: Linat-an
description: The dish is a traditional pork stew. It characteristically uses pork ribs (or other bony cuts of pork) boiled and simmered until very tender, lemongrass, string beans, and starchy ingredients for a thicker soup (usually taro).

name: Lobby
description: The dish is a traditional stew or casserole, containing corned beef, potatoes and onion.

name: Lunggoi Katsa
description: The dish is composed of stewed sheep's head, with curry, fennel, monosodium glutamate and salt.

name: Molagoottal
description: The dish is a stew with coconut and lentils as a base.

name: Sonofabitch stew
description: The dish is a cowboy dish. Various recipes exist for this beef stew, and some sources say its ingredients may vary according to whatever is on hand.

name: Sagamite
description: The dish is made from hominy, cornmeal, or Indian corn and grease (from animal fat).

name: Mulligan stew
description: The dish is broadly defined as a stew made of odds and ends or any available ingredients.

name: Ollada
description: The dish is a stew of potatoes, beans and cabbage or turnips.

name: Ostrich stew
description: This dish is a stew prepared using ostrich meat as a primary ingredient. The meat can be diced into cubes, and leg meat from the ostrich is sometimes used.

name: Purin
description: The dish is custard pudding.

name: Gionbō
description: This sweet is made using a particular variety of dried persimmon, and has the filling made from a soft form of rice cake with bean jam, then sprinkling white sugar over it.

name: Gyūhi
description: This sweet is a softer variety of rice cake, which is made from either glutinous rice itself or from glutinous rice flour.

name: Chinese flaky pastry
description: The dish is a form of unleavened flaky pastry. There are 2 versions, but both forms require creating two doughs: a "water" dough and an "oil" dough. The "water" dough requires mixing of flour, oil or fat, and warm water at a ratio of 10:3:4, while the "oil" dough requires direct mixing of flour and oil or fat at a ratio of 2:1 or 3:1, which provides for a crumbly mouthfeel and rich flavour. The two types of dough are systematically folded and rolled out to form multiple laminated layers of flaky dough, filled with various fillings, and baked at a temperature between 180 and 220 °C (356 and 428 °F)

name: Colston bun
description: The dish is a sweet bun made of a yeast dough flavoured with dried fruit such as currants, candied peel, and sweet spices.

name: Currant bun
description: The dish is a sweet bun that contains currants or raisins.

name: London bun
description: The dish is a square-shaped bun made of rich yeast dough flavored with currants and candied peel topped with white sugar icing or crystallised sugar.

name: Spiced bun
description: The dish is a sweet bun to which spices were added during the baking process.

name: Penny bun
description: The dish is a small bread bun or loaf.

name: Fläsklägg med rotmos
description: The dish consists cured ham hock is cooked for one to two hours together with onions, carrots, and allspice or similar vegetable. Rutabaga, potatoes and carrots are then diced and cooked soft in the broth, then drained and mashed. It may be served with different kinds of mustard; the preferred one is a traditional sweet mustard.

name: Amish preaching soup
description: The dish is a type of bean soup. Some versions are prepared with beans and ham hocks.

name: Yun dou juan
description: This dish is a traditional dish made by boiling kidney beans and then steaming them. The beans are crushed into a paste, shaped into rectangles, layered with bean paste, and rolled up; the rolls are then sliced into smaller pieces for serving.

name: Ulava charu
description: This dish is a soup like dish made with horse gram. The horse gram is boiled in water with salt, then strained from the soup before serving.

name: Purtumute
description: The dish is prepared by stewing several types of beans and corn, seasoned made with coriander.

name: Kulen
description: The sausage is made of minced pork.

name: Chilorio
description: This dish is generally made from pork fried in chili sauce.

name: Frijoles Puercos
description: This dish is characterized by blended beans stewed with lard, chile pepper, chorizo, Chihuahua cheese.

name: Rauchkäse
description: This is a type of smoked cheese, known for being semi-soft with a smoky brown rind. It is typically smoked using birch or spruce woods.

name: Balyk
description: The dish is the salted and dried soft parts of fish, usually coming from large valuable species. Over time, the term was applied to smoked fish of this kind.

name: Bijajica
description: The dish is made by cassava starch, eggs, and sugar, fried in lard.

name: Manjar branco
description: The dish is pudding mold with coconut extract.

name: Sač
description: The dish refer to a dish made of meat, vegetable and potatoes, baked in it.

name: Bacalhau com natas
description: The dish is made of salted cod baked with onions, diced potatoes, and double cream.

name: Chanfana
description: The dish is a old goat meat roasted in wood-fired ovens.

name: Catatos
description: The dish is made with fried caterpillars and garlic. It is often served over rice.

name: Maboké
description: It is a fish dish, with roasted spices, wrapped in banana leaf.

name: Rolex
description: The food is prepared by combining an egg omelette and vegetables wrapped in a flatbread. This single-portion dish is quick to prepare and can be eaten at any time of the day, from breakfast to lunch or supper or a snack.
